2290void Builtins::Generate_ReflectApply(MacroAssembler* masm) {
2291 // ----------- S t a t e -------------
2292 // -- r3 : argc
2293 // -- sp[0] : receiver
2294 // -- sp[4] : target (if argc >= 1)
2295 // -- sp[8] : thisArgument (if argc >= 2)
2296 // -- sp[12] : argumentsList (if argc == 3)
2297 // -----------------------------------
2298
2299 // 1. Load target into r4 (if present), argumentsList into r5 (if present),
2300 // remove all arguments from the stack (including the receiver), and push
2301 // thisArgument (if present) instead.
2302 {
2303 __ LoadRoot(r4, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
2304 __ mr(r8, r4);
2305 __ mr(r5, r4);
2306
2307 Label done;
2308 __ CmpS64(r3, Operand(JSParameterCount(1)), r0);
2309 __ blt(&done);
2310 __ LoadU64(r4, MemOperand(sp, kSystemPointerSize)); // thisArg
2311 __ CmpS64(r3, Operand(JSParameterCount(2)), r0);
2312 __ blt(&done);
2313 __ LoadU64(r8, MemOperand(sp, 2 * kSystemPointerSize)); // argArray
2314 __ CmpS64(r3, Operand(JSParameterCount(3)), r0);
2315 __ blt(&done);
2316 __ LoadU64(r5, MemOperand(sp, 3 * kSystemPointerSize)); // argArray
2317
2318 __ bind(&done);
2319 __ DropArgumentsAndPushNewReceiver(r3, r8);
2320 }
2321
2322 // ----------- S t a t e -------------
2323 // -- r5 : argumentsList
2324 // -- r4 : target
2325 // -- sp[0] : thisArgument
2326 // -----------------------------------
2327
2328 // 2. We don't need to check explicitly for callable target here,
2329 // since that's the first thing the Call/CallWithArrayLike builtins
2330 // will do.
2331
2332 // 3. Apply the target to the given argumentsList.
2333 __ TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kCallWithArrayLike);
2334}

2336void Builtins::Generate_ReflectConstruct(MacroAssembler* masm) {
2337 // ----------- S t a t e -------------
2338 // -- r3 : argc
2339 // -- sp[0] : receiver
2340 // -- sp[4] : target
2341 // -- sp[8] : argumentsList
2342 // -- sp[12] : new.target (optional)
2343 // -----------------------------------
2344
2345 // 1. Load target into r4 (if present), argumentsList into r5 (if present),
2346 // new.target into r6 (if present, otherwise use target), remove all
2347 // arguments from the stack (including the receiver), and push thisArgument
2348 // (if present) instead.
2349 {
2350 __ LoadRoot(r4, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
2351 __ mr(r5, r4);
2352
2353 Label done;
2354 __ mr(r7, r4);
2355 __ CmpS64(r3, Operand(JSParameterCount(1)), r0);
2356 __ blt(&done);
2357 __ LoadU64(r4, MemOperand(sp, kSystemPointerSize)); // thisArg
2358 __ mr(r6, r4);
2359 __ CmpS64(r3, Operand(JSParameterCount(2)), r0);
2360 __ blt(&done);
2361 __ LoadU64(r5, MemOperand(sp, 2 * kSystemPointerSize)); // argArray
2362 __ CmpS64(r3, Operand(JSParameterCount(3)), r0);
2363 __ blt(&done);
2364 __ LoadU64(r6, MemOperand(sp, 3 * kSystemPointerSize)); // argArray
2365 __ bind(&done);
2366 __ DropArgumentsAndPushNewReceiver(r3, r7);
2367 }
2368
2369 // ----------- S t a t e -------------
2370 // -- r5 : argumentsList
2371 // -- r6 : new.target
2372 // -- r4 : target
2373 // -- sp[0] : receiver (undefined)
2374 // -----------------------------------
2375
2376 // 2. We don't need to check explicitly for constructor target here,
2377 // since that's the first thing the Construct/ConstructWithArrayLike
2378 // builtins will do.
2379
2380 // 3. We don't need to check explicitly for constructor new.target here,
2381 // since that's the second thing the Construct/ConstructWithArrayLike
2382 // builtins will do.
2383
2384 // 4. Construct the target with the given new.target and argumentsList.
2385 __ TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kConstructWithArrayLike);
2386}

2390// Allocate new stack space for |count| arguments and shift all existing
2391// arguments already on the stack. |pointer_to_new_space_out| points to the
2392// first free slot on the stack to copy additional arguments to and
2393// |argc_in_out| is updated to include |count|.
2394void Generate_AllocateSpaceAndShiftExistingArguments(
2395 MacroAssembler* masm, Register count, Register argc_in_out,
2396 Register pointer_to_new_space_out, Register scratch1, Register scratch2) {
2397 DCHECK(!AreAliased(count, argc_in_out, pointer_to_new_space_out, scratch1,
2398 scratch2));
2399 Register old_sp = scratch1;
2400 Register new_space = scratch2;
2401 __ addi(old_sp, sp, Operand(-kSystemPointerSize));
2402 __ ShiftLeftU64(new_space, count, Operand(kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
2403 __ AllocateStackSpace(new_space);
2404
2405 Register dest = pointer_to_new_space_out;
2406 __ addi(dest, sp, Operand(-kSystemPointerSize));
2407 Label loop, skip;
2408 __ mr(r0, argc_in_out);
2409 __ cmpi(r0, Operand::Zero());
2410 __ ble(&skip);
2411 __ mtctr(r0);
2412 __ bind(&loop);
2413 __ LoadU64WithUpdate(r0, MemOperand(old_sp, kSystemPointerSize));
2414 __ StoreU64WithUpdate(r0, MemOperand(dest, kSystemPointerSize));
2415 __ bdnz(&loop);
2416
2417 __ bind(&skip);
2418 // Update total number of arguments, restore dest.
2419 __ add(argc_in_out, argc_in_out, count);
2420 __ addi(dest, dest, Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
2421}

2425// static
2426// TODO(v8:11615): Observe Code::kMaxArguments in CallOrConstructVarargs
2427void Builtins::Generate_CallOrConstructVarargs(MacroAssembler* masm,
2428 Builtin target_builtin) {
2429 // ----------- S t a t e -------------
2430 // -- r4 : target
2431 // -- r3 : number of parameters on the stack
2432 // -- r5 : arguments list (a FixedArray)
2433 // -- r7 : len (number of elements to push from args)
2434 // -- r6 : new.target (for [[Construct]])
2435 // -----------------------------------
2436
2437 Register scratch = ip;
2438
2439 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
2440 // Allow r5 to be a FixedArray, or a FixedDoubleArray if r7 == 0.
2441 Label ok, fail;
2442 __ AssertNotSmi(r5);
2443 __ LoadTaggedField(scratch, FieldMemOperand(r5, HeapObject::kMapOffset),
2444 r0);
2445 __ LoadU16(scratch, FieldMemOperand(scratch, Map::kInstanceTypeOffset));
2446 __ cmpi(scratch, Operand(FIXED_ARRAY_TYPE));
2447 __ beq(&ok);
2448 __ cmpi(scratch, Operand(FIXED_DOUBLE_ARRAY_TYPE));
2449 __ bne(&fail);
2450 __ cmpi(r7, Operand::Zero());
2451 __ beq(&ok);
2452 // Fall through.
2453 __ bind(&fail);
2454 __ Abort(AbortReason::kOperandIsNotAFixedArray);
2455
2456 __ bind(&ok);
2457 }
2458
2459 // Check for stack overflow.
2460 Label stack_overflow;
2461 __ StackOverflowCheck(r7, scratch, &stack_overflow);
2462
2463 // Move the arguments already in the stack,
2464 // including the receiver and the return address.
2465 // r7: Number of arguments to make room for.
2466 // r3: Number of arguments already on the stack.
2467 // r8: Points to first free slot on the stack after arguments were shifted.
2468 Generate_AllocateSpaceAndShiftExistingArguments(masm, r7, r3, r8, ip, r9);
2469
2470 // Push arguments onto the stack (thisArgument is already on the stack).
2471 {
2472 Label loop, no_args, skip;
2473 __ cmpi(r7, Operand::Zero());
2474 __ beq(&no_args);
2475 __ addi(r5, r5,
2476 Operand(OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedArray) - kHeapObjectTag -
2477 kTaggedSize));
2478 __ mtctr(r7);
2479 __ bind(&loop);
2480 __ LoadTaggedField(scratch, MemOperand(r5, kTaggedSize), r0);
2481 __ addi(r5, r5, Operand(kTaggedSize));
2482 __ CompareRoot(scratch, RootIndex::kTheHoleValue);
2483 __ bne(&skip);
2484 __ LoadRoot(scratch, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
2485 __ bind(&skip);
2486 __ StoreU64(scratch, MemOperand(r8));
2487 __ addi(r8, r8, Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
2488 __ bdnz(&loop);
2489 __ bind(&no_args);
2490 }
2491
2492 // Tail-call to the actual Call or Construct builtin.
2493 __ TailCallBuiltin(target_builtin);
2494
2495 __ bind(&stack_overflow);
2496 __ TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowStackOverflow);
2497}
2498
2499// static
2500void Builtins::Generate_CallOrConstructForwardVarargs(MacroAssembler* masm,
2501 CallOrConstructMode mode,
2502 Builtin target_builtin) {
2503 // ----------- S t a t e -------------
2504 // -- r3 : the number of arguments
2505 // -- r6 : the new.target (for [[Construct]] calls)
2506 // -- r4 : the target to call (can be any Object)
2507 // -- r5 : start index (to support rest parameters)
2508 // -----------------------------------
2509
2510 Register scratch = r9;
2511
2512 if (mode == CallOrConstructMode::kConstruct) {
2513 Label new_target_constructor, new_target_not_constructor;
2514 __ JumpIfSmi(r6, &new_target_not_constructor);
2515 __ LoadTaggedField(scratch, FieldMemOperand(r6, HeapObject::kMapOffset),
2516 r0);
2517 __ lbz(scratch, FieldMemOperand(scratch, Map::kBitFieldOffset));
2518 __ TestBit(scratch, Map::Bits1::IsConstructorBit::kShift, r0);
2519 __ bne(&new_target_constructor, cr0);
2520 __ bind(&new_target_not_constructor);
2521 {
2522 FrameScope scope(masm, StackFrame::MANUAL);
2523 __ EnterFrame(StackFrame::INTERNAL);
2524 __ Push(r6);
2525 __ CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowNotConstructor);
2526 __ Trap(); // Unreachable.
2527 }
2528 __ bind(&new_target_constructor);
2529 }
2530
2531 Label stack_done, stack_overflow;
2532 __ LoadU64(r8, MemOperand(fp, StandardFrameConstants::kArgCOffset));
2533 __ subi(r8, r8, Operand(kJSArgcReceiverSlots));
2534 __ sub(r8, r8, r5, LeaveOE, SetRC);
2535 __ ble(&stack_done, cr0);
2536 {
2537 // ----------- S t a t e -------------
2538 // -- r3 : the number of arguments already in the stack
2539 // -- r4 : the target to call (can be any Object)
2540 // -- r5 : start index (to support rest parameters)
2541 // -- r6 : the new.target (for [[Construct]] calls)
2542 // -- fp : point to the caller stack frame
2543 // -- r8 : number of arguments to copy, i.e. arguments count - start index
2544 // -----------------------------------
2545
2546 // Check for stack overflow.
2547 __ StackOverflowCheck(r8, scratch, &stack_overflow);
2548
2549 // Forward the arguments from the caller frame.
2550 // Point to the first argument to copy (skipping the receiver).
2551 __ addi(r7, fp,
2552 Operand(CommonFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeAboveFp +
2553 kSystemPointerSize));
2554 __ ShiftLeftU64(scratch, r5, Operand(kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
2555 __ add(r7, r7, scratch);
2556
2557 // Move the arguments already in the stack,
2558 // including the receiver and the return address.
2559 // r8: Number of arguments to make room for.
2560 // r3: Number of arguments already on the stack.
2561 // r5: Points to first free slot on the stack after arguments were shifted.
2562 Generate_AllocateSpaceAndShiftExistingArguments(masm, r8, r3, r5, scratch,
2563 ip);
2564
2565 // Copy arguments from the caller frame.
2566 // TODO(victorgomes): Consider using forward order as potentially more cache
2567 // friendly.
2568 {
2569 Label loop;
2570 __ bind(&loop);
2571 {
2572 __ subi(r8, r8, Operand(1));
2573 __ ShiftLeftU64(scratch, r8, Operand(kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
2574 __ LoadU64(r0, MemOperand(r7, scratch));
2575 __ StoreU64(r0, MemOperand(r5, scratch));
2576 __ cmpi(r8, Operand::Zero());
2577 __ bne(&loop);
2578 }
2579 }
2580 }
2581 __ bind(&stack_done);
2582 // Tail-call to the actual Call or Construct builtin.
2583 __ TailCallBuiltin(target_builtin);
2584
2585 __ bind(&stack_overflow);
2586 __ TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowStackOverflow);
2587}

2589// static
2590void Builtins::Generate_CallFunction(MacroAssembler* masm,
2591 ConvertReceiverMode mode) {
2592 // ----------- S t a t e -------------
2593 // -- r3 : the number of arguments
2594 // -- r4 : the function to call (checked to be a JSFunction)
2595 // -----------------------------------
2596 __ AssertCallableFunction(r4);
2597
2598 __ LoadTaggedField(
2599 r5, FieldMemOperand(r4, JSFunction::kSharedFunctionInfoOffset), r0);
2600
2601 // Enter the context of the function; ToObject has to run in the function
2602 // context, and we also need to take the global proxy from the function
2603 // context in case of conversion.
2604 __ LoadTaggedField(cp, FieldMemOperand(r4, JSFunction::kContextOffset), r0);
2605 // We need to convert the receiver for non-native sloppy mode functions.
2606 Label done_convert;
2607 __ lwz(r6, FieldMemOperand(r5, SharedFunctionInfo::kFlagsOffset));
2608 __ andi(r0, r6,
2609 Operand(SharedFunctionInfo::IsStrictBit::kMask |
2610 SharedFunctionInfo::IsNativeBit::kMask));
2611 __ bne(&done_convert, cr0);
2612 {
2613 // ----------- S t a t e -------------
2614 // -- r3 : the number of arguments
2615 // -- r4 : the function to call (checked to be a JSFunction)
2616 // -- r5 : the shared function info.
2617 // -- cp : the function context.
2618 // -----------------------------------
2619
2620 if (mode == ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined) {
2621 // Patch receiver to global proxy.
2622 __ LoadGlobalProxy(r6);
2623 } else {
2624 Label convert_to_object, convert_receiver;
2625 __ LoadReceiver(r6);
2626 __ JumpIfSmi(r6, &convert_to_object);
2627 static_assert(LAST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE == LAST_TYPE);
2628 __ CompareObjectType(r6, r7, r7, FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE);
2629 __ bge(&done_convert);
2630 if (mode != ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined) {
2631 Label convert_global_proxy;
2632 __ JumpIfRoot(r6, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue, &convert_global_proxy);
2633 __ JumpIfNotRoot(r6, RootIndex::kNullValue, &convert_to_object);
2634 __ bind(&convert_global_proxy);
2635 {
2636 // Patch receiver to global proxy.
2637 __ LoadGlobalProxy(r6);
2638 }
2639 __ b(&convert_receiver);
2640 }
2641 __ bind(&convert_to_object);
2642 {
2643 // Convert receiver using ToObject.
2644 // TODO(bmeurer): Inline the allocation here to avoid building the frame
2645 // in the fast case? (fall back to AllocateInNewSpace?)
2646 FrameAndConstantPoolScope scope(masm, StackFrame::INTERNAL);
2647 __ SmiTag(r3);
2648 __ Push(r3, r4);
2649 __ mr(r3, r6);
2650 __ Push(cp);
2651 __ CallBuiltin(Builtin::kToObject);
2652 __ Pop(cp);
2653 __ mr(r6, r3);
2654 __ Pop(r3, r4);
2655 __ SmiUntag(r3);
2656 }
2657 __ LoadTaggedField(
2658 r5, FieldMemOperand(r4, JSFunction::kSharedFunctionInfoOffset), r0);
2659 __ bind(&convert_receiver);
2660 }
2661 __ StoreReceiver(r6);
2662 }
2663 __ bind(&done_convert);
2664
2665 // ----------- S t a t e -------------
2666 // -- r3 : the number of arguments
2667 // -- r4 : the function to call (checked to be a JSFunction)
2668 // -- r5 : the shared function info.
2669 // -- cp : the function context.
2670 // -----------------------------------
2671
2672 __ LoadU16(
2673 r5, FieldMemOperand(r5, SharedFunctionInfo::kFormalParameterCountOffset));
2674 __ InvokeFunctionCode(r4, no_reg, r5, r3, InvokeType::kJump);
2675}

2677namespace {
2678
2679void Generate_PushBoundArguments(MacroAssembler* masm) {
2680 // ----------- S t a t e -------------
2681 // -- r3 : the number of arguments
2682 // -- r4 : target (checked to be a JSBoundFunction)
2683 // -- r6 : new.target (only in case of [[Construct]])
2684 // -----------------------------------
2685
2686 // Load [[BoundArguments]] into r5 and length of that into r7.
2687 Label no_bound_arguments;
2688 __ LoadTaggedField(
2689 r5, FieldMemOperand(r4, JSBoundFunction::kBoundArgumentsOffset), r0);
2690 __ SmiUntag(r7, FieldMemOperand(r5, offsetof(FixedArray, length_)), SetRC,
2691 r0);
2692 __ beq(&no_bound_arguments, cr0);
2693 {
2694 // ----------- S t a t e -------------
2695 // -- r3 : the number of arguments
2696 // -- r4 : target (checked to be a JSBoundFunction)
2697 // -- r5 : the [[BoundArguments]] (implemented as FixedArray)
2698 // -- r6 : new.target (only in case of [[Construct]])
2699 // -- r7 : the number of [[BoundArguments]]
2700 // -----------------------------------
2701
2702 Register scratch = r9;
2703 // Reserve stack space for the [[BoundArguments]].
2704 {
2705 Label done;
2706 __ ShiftLeftU64(r10, r7, Operand(kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
2707 __ sub(r0, sp, r10);
2708 // Check the stack for overflow. We are not trying to catch interruptions
2709 // (i.e. debug break and preemption) here, so check the "real stack
2710 // limit".
2711 {
2712 __ LoadStackLimit(scratch, StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit, ip);
2713 __ CmpU64(r0, scratch);
2714 }
2715 __ bgt(&done); // Signed comparison.
2716 {
2717 FrameScope scope(masm, StackFrame::MANUAL);
2718 __ EnterFrame(StackFrame::INTERNAL);
2719 __ CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowStackOverflow);
2720 }
2721 __ bind(&done);
2722 }
2723
2724 // Pop receiver.
2725 __ Pop(r8);
2726
2727 // Push [[BoundArguments]].
2728 {
2729 Label loop, done;
2730 __ add(r3, r3, r7); // Adjust effective number of arguments.
2731 __ addi(r5, r5,
2732 Operand(OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedArray) - kHeapObjectTag));
2733 __ mtctr(r7);
2734
2735 __ bind(&loop);
2736 __ subi(r7, r7, Operand(1));
2737 __ ShiftLeftU64(scratch, r7, Operand(kTaggedSizeLog2));
2738 __ add(scratch, scratch, r5);
2739 __ LoadTaggedField(scratch, MemOperand(scratch), r0);
2740 __ Push(scratch);
2741 __ bdnz(&loop);
2742 __ bind(&done);
2743 }
2744
2745 // Push receiver.
2746 __ Push(r8);
2747 }
2748 __ bind(&no_bound_arguments);
2749}

2758 // -----------------------------------

2760

2762 __ LoadTaggedField(r6, FieldMemOperand(r4, JSBoundFunction::kBoundThisOffset),

2764 __ StoreReceiver(r6);

2775// static
2776void Builtins::Generate_Call(MacroAssembler* masm, ConvertReceiverMode mode) {
2777 // ----------- S t a t e -------------
2778 // -- r3 : the number of arguments
2779 // -- r4 : the target to call (can be any Object).
2780 // -----------------------------------
2781 Register target = r4;
2782 Register map = r7;
2783 Register instance_type = r8;
2784 Register scratch = r9;
2785 DCHECK(!AreAliased(r3, target, map, instance_type));
2786
2787 Label non_callable, class_constructor;
2788 __ JumpIfSmi(target, &non_callable);
2789 __ LoadMap(map, target);
2790 __ CompareInstanceTypeRange(map, instance_type, scratch,
2791 FIRST_CALLABLE_JS_FUNCTION_TYPE,
2792 LAST_CALLABLE_JS_FUNCTION_TYPE);
2793 __ TailCallBuiltin(Builtins::CallFunction(mode), le);
2794 __ cmpi(instance_type, Operand(JS_BOUND_FUNCTION_TYPE));
2795 __ TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kCallBoundFunction, eq);
2796
2797 // Check if target has a [[Call]] internal method.
2798 {
2799 Register flags = r7;
2800 __ lbz(flags, FieldMemOperand(map, Map::kBitFieldOffset));
2801 map = no_reg;
2802 __ TestBit(flags, Map::Bits1::IsCallableBit::kShift, r0);
2803 __ beq(&non_callable, cr0);
2804 }
2805
2806 // Check if target is a proxy and call CallProxy external builtin
2807 __ cmpi(instance_type, Operand(JS_PROXY_TYPE));
2808 __ TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kCallProxy, eq);
2809
2810 // Check if target is a wrapped function and call CallWrappedFunction external
2811 // builtin
2812 __ cmpi(instance_type, Operand(JS_WRAPPED_FUNCTION_TYPE));
2813 __ TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kCallWrappedFunction, eq);
2814
2815 // ES6 section 9.2.1 [[Call]] ( thisArgument, argumentsList)
2816 // Check that the function is not a "classConstructor".
2817 __ cmpi(instance_type, Operand(JS_CLASS_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE));
2818 __ beq(&class_constructor);
2819
2820 // 2. Call to something else, which might have a [[Call]] internal method (if
2821 // not we raise an exception).
2822 // Overwrite the original receiver the (original) target.
2823 __ StoreReceiver(target);
2824 // Let the "call_as_function_delegate" take care of the rest.
2825 __ LoadNativeContextSlot(target, Context::CALL_AS_FUNCTION_DELEGATE_INDEX);
2826 __ TailCallBuiltin(
2827 Builtins::CallFunction(ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined));
2828
2829 // 3. Call to something that is not callable.
2830 __ bind(&non_callable);
2831 {
2832 FrameAndConstantPoolScope scope(masm, StackFrame::INTERNAL);
2833 __ Push(target);
2834 __ CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowCalledNonCallable);
2835 __ Trap(); // Unreachable.
2836 }
2837
2838 // 4. The function is a "classConstructor", need to raise an exception.
2839 __ bind(&class_constructor);
2840 {
2841 FrameAndConstantPoolScope scope(masm, StackFrame::INTERNAL);
2842 __ Push(target);
2843 __ CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowConstructorNonCallableError);
2844 __ Trap(); // Unreachable.
2845 }
2846}

2848// static
2849void Builtins::Generate_ConstructFunction(MacroAssembler* masm) {
2850 // ----------- S t a t e -------------
2851 // -- r3 : the number of arguments
2852 // -- r4 : the constructor to call (checked to be a JSFunction)
2853 // -- r6 : the new target (checked to be a constructor)
2854 // -----------------------------------
2855 __ AssertConstructor(r4);
2856 __ AssertFunction(r4);
2857
2858 // Calling convention for function specific ConstructStubs require
2859 // r5 to contain either an AllocationSite or undefined.
2860 __ LoadRoot(r5, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
2861
2862 Label call_generic_stub;
2863
2864 // Jump to JSBuiltinsConstructStub or JSConstructStubGeneric.
2865 __ LoadTaggedField(
2866 r7, FieldMemOperand(r4, JSFunction::kSharedFunctionInfoOffset), r0);
2867 __ lwz(r7, FieldMemOperand(r7, SharedFunctionInfo::kFlagsOffset));
2868 __ mov(ip, Operand(SharedFunctionInfo::ConstructAsBuiltinBit::kMask));
2869 __ and_(r7, r7, ip, SetRC);
2870 __ beq(&call_generic_stub, cr0);
2871
2872 __ TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kJSBuiltinsConstructStub);
2873
2874 __ bind(&call_generic_stub);
2875 __ TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kJSConstructStubGeneric);
2876}

2878// static
2879void Builtins::Generate_ConstructBoundFunction(MacroAssembler* masm) {
2880 // ----------- S t a t e -------------
2881 // -- r3 : the number of arguments
2882 // -- r4 : the function to call (checked to be a JSBoundFunction)
2883 // -- r6 : the new target (checked to be a constructor)
2884 // -----------------------------------
2885 __ AssertConstructor(r4);
2886 __ AssertBoundFunction(r4);
2887
2888 // Push the [[BoundArguments]] onto the stack.
2889 Generate_PushBoundArguments(masm);
2890
2891 // Patch new.target to [[BoundTargetFunction]] if new.target equals target.
2892 Label skip;
2893 __ CompareTagged(r4, r6);
2894 __ bne(&skip);
2895 __ LoadTaggedField(
2896 r6, FieldMemOperand(r4, JSBoundFunction::kBoundTargetFunctionOffset), r0);
2897 __ bind(&skip);
2898
2899 // Construct the [[BoundTargetFunction]] via the Construct builtin.
2900 __ LoadTaggedField(
2901 r4, FieldMemOperand(r4, JSBoundFunction::kBoundTargetFunctionOffset), r0);
2902 __ TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kConstruct);
2903}

2905// static
2906void Builtins::Generate_Construct(MacroAssembler* masm) {
2907 // ----------- S t a t e -------------
2908 // -- r3 : the number of arguments
2909 // -- r4 : the constructor to call (can be any Object)
2910 // -- r6 : the new target (either the same as the constructor or
2911 // the JSFunction on which new was invoked initially)
2912 // -----------------------------------
2913 Register target = r4;
2914 Register map = r7;
2915 Register instance_type = r8;
2916 Register scratch = r9;
2917 DCHECK(!AreAliased(r3, target, map, instance_type, scratch));
2918
2919 // Check if target is a Smi.
2920 Label non_constructor, non_proxy;
2921 __ JumpIfSmi(target, &non_constructor);
2922
2923 // Check if target has a [[Construct]] internal method.
2924 __ LoadTaggedField(map, FieldMemOperand(target, HeapObject::kMapOffset), r0);
2925 {
2926 Register flags = r5;
2927 DCHECK(!AreAliased(r3, target, map, instance_type, flags));
2928 __ lbz(flags, FieldMemOperand(map, Map::kBitFieldOffset));
2929 __ TestBit(flags, Map::Bits1::IsConstructorBit::kShift, r0);
2930 __ beq(&non_constructor, cr0);
2931 }
2932
2933 // Dispatch based on instance type.
2934 __ CompareInstanceTypeRange(map, instance_type, scratch,
2935 FIRST_JS_FUNCTION_TYPE, LAST_JS_FUNCTION_TYPE);
2936 __ TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kConstructFunction, le);
2937
2938 // Only dispatch to bound functions after checking whether they are
2939 // constructors.
2940 __ cmpi(instance_type, Operand(JS_BOUND_FUNCTION_TYPE));
2941 __ TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kConstructBoundFunction, eq);
2942
2943 // Only dispatch to proxies after checking whether they are constructors.
2944 __ cmpi(instance_type, Operand(JS_PROXY_TYPE));
2945 __ bne(&non_proxy);
2946 __ TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kConstructProxy);
2947
2948 // Called Construct on an exotic Object with a [[Construct]] internal method.
2949 __ bind(&non_proxy);
2950 {
2951 // Overwrite the original receiver with the (original) target.
2952 __ StoreReceiver(target);
2953 // Let the "call_as_constructor_delegate" take care of the rest.
2954 __ LoadNativeContextSlot(target,
2955 Context::CALL_AS_CONSTRUCTOR_DELEGATE_INDEX);
2956 __ TailCallBuiltin(Builtins::CallFunction());
2957 }
2958
2959 // Called Construct on an Object that doesn't have a [[Construct]] internal
2960 // method.
2961 __ bind(&non_constructor);
2962 __ TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kConstructedNonConstructable);
2963}

2967struct SaveWasmParamsScope {
2968 explicit SaveWasmParamsScope(MacroAssembler* masm) : masm(masm) {
2969 for (Register gp_param_reg : wasm::kGpParamRegisters) {
2970 gp_regs.set(gp_param_reg);
2971 }
2972 for (DoubleRegister fp_param_reg : wasm::kFpParamRegisters) {
2973 fp_regs.set(fp_param_reg);
2974 }
2975
2976 CHECK_EQ(gp_regs.Count(), arraysize(wasm::kGpParamRegisters));
2977 CHECK_EQ(fp_regs.Count(), arraysize(wasm::kFpParamRegisters));
2978 CHECK_EQ(simd_regs.Count(), arraysize(wasm::kFpParamRegisters));
2979 CHECK_EQ(WasmLiftoffSetupFrameConstants::kNumberOfSavedGpParamRegs + 1,
2980 gp_regs.Count());
2981 CHECK_EQ(WasmLiftoffSetupFrameConstants::kNumberOfSavedFpParamRegs,
2982 fp_regs.Count());
2983 CHECK_EQ(WasmLiftoffSetupFrameConstants::kNumberOfSavedFpParamRegs,
2984 simd_regs.Count());
2985
2986 __ MultiPush(gp_regs);
2987 __ MultiPushF64AndV128(fp_regs, simd_regs, ip, r0);
2988 }
2989 ~SaveWasmParamsScope() {
2990 __ MultiPopF64AndV128(fp_regs, simd_regs, ip, r0);
2991 __ MultiPop(gp_regs);
2992 }
2993
2994 RegList gp_regs;
2995 DoubleRegList fp_regs;
2996 // List must match register numbers under kFpParamRegisters.
2997 Simd128RegList simd_regs = {v1, v2, v3, v4, v5, v6, v7, v8};
2998 MacroAssembler* masm;
2999};

3001void Builtins::Generate_WasmLiftoffFrameSetup(MacroAssembler* masm) {
3002 Register func_index = wasm::kLiftoffFrameSetupFunctionReg;
3003 Register vector = r11;
3004 Register scratch = ip;
3005 Label allocate_vector, done;
3006
3007 __ LoadTaggedField(
3008 vector,
3009 FieldMemOperand(kWasmImplicitArgRegister,
3010 WasmTrustedInstanceData::kFeedbackVectorsOffset),
3011 scratch);
3012 __ ShiftLeftU64(scratch, func_index, Operand(kTaggedSizeLog2));
3013 __ AddS64(vector, vector, scratch);
3014 __ LoadTaggedField(vector,
3015 FieldMemOperand(vector, OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedArray)),
3016 scratch);
3017 __ JumpIfSmi(vector, &allocate_vector);
3018 __ bind(&done);
3019 __ push(kWasmImplicitArgRegister);
3020 __ push(vector);
3021 __ Ret();
3022
3023 __ bind(&allocate_vector);
3024
3025 // Feedback vector doesn't exist yet. Call the runtime to allocate it.
3026 // We temporarily change the frame type for this, because we need special
3027 // handling by the stack walker in case of GC.
3028 __ mov(scratch,
3029 Operand(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(StackFrame::WASM_LIFTOFF_SETUP)));
3030 __ StoreU64(scratch, MemOperand(sp));
3031
3032 // Save current return address as it will get clobbered during CallRuntime.
3033 __ mflr(scratch);
3034 __ push(scratch);
3035 {
3036 SaveWasmParamsScope save_params(masm); // Will use r0 and ip as scratch.
3037 // Arguments to the runtime function: instance data, func_index.
3038 __ push(kWasmImplicitArgRegister);
3039 __ SmiTag(func_index);
3040 __ push(func_index);
3041 // Allocate a stack slot where the runtime function can spill a pointer
3042 // to the {NativeModule}.
3043 __ push(r11);
3044 __ LoadSmiLiteral(cp, Smi::zero());
3045 __ CallRuntime(Runtime::kWasmAllocateFeedbackVector, 3);
3046 __ mr(vector, kReturnRegister0);
3047 // Saved parameters are restored at the end of this block.
3048 }
3049 __ pop(scratch);
3050 __ mtlr(scratch);
3051
3052 __ mov(scratch, Operand(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(StackFrame::WASM)));
3053 __ StoreU64(scratch, MemOperand(sp));
3054 __ b(&done);
3055}
3056
3057void Builtins::Generate_WasmCompileLazy(MacroAssembler* masm) {
3058 // The function index was put in a register by the jump table trampoline.
3059 // Convert to Smi for the runtime call.
3060 __ SmiTag(kWasmCompileLazyFuncIndexRegister);
3061
3062 {
3063 HardAbortScope hard_abort(masm); // Avoid calls to Abort.
3064 FrameAndConstantPoolScope scope(masm, StackFrame::INTERNAL);
3065
3066 {
3067 SaveWasmParamsScope save_params(masm); // Will use r0 and ip as scratch.
3068
3069 // Push the instance data as an explicit argument to the runtime function.
3070 __ push(kWasmImplicitArgRegister);
3071 // Push the function index as second argument.
3072 __ push(kWasmCompileLazyFuncIndexRegister);
3073 // Initialize the JavaScript context with 0. CEntry will use it to
3074 // set the current context on the isolate.
3075 __ LoadSmiLiteral(cp, Smi::zero());
3076 __ CallRuntime(Runtime::kWasmCompileLazy, 2);
3077 // The runtime function returns the jump table slot offset as a Smi. Use
3078 // that to compute the jump target in r11.
3079 __ SmiUntag(kReturnRegister0);
3080 __ mr(r11, kReturnRegister0);
3081
3082 // Saved parameters are restored at the end of this block.
3083 }
3084
3085 // After the instance data register has been restored, we can add the jump
3086 // table start to the jump table offset already stored in r11.
3087 __ LoadU64(ip,
3088 FieldMemOperand(kWasmImplicitArgRegister,
3089 WasmTrustedInstanceData::kJumpTableStartOffset),
3090 r0);
3091 __ AddS64(r11, r11, ip);
3092 }
3093
3094 // Finally, jump to the jump table slot for the function.
3095 __ Jump(r11);
3096}
3097
3098void Builtins::Generate_WasmDebugBreak(MacroAssembler* masm) {
3099 HardAbortScope hard_abort(masm); // Avoid calls to Abort.
3100 {
3101 FrameAndConstantPoolScope scope(masm, StackFrame::WASM_DEBUG_BREAK);
3102
3103 // Save all parameter registers. They might hold live values, we restore
3104 // them after the runtime call.
3105 __ MultiPush(WasmDebugBreakFrameConstants::kPushedGpRegs);
3106 __ MultiPushF64AndV128(WasmDebugBreakFrameConstants::kPushedFpRegs,
3107 WasmDebugBreakFrameConstants::kPushedSimd128Regs, ip,
3108 r0);
3109
3110 // Initialize the JavaScript context with 0. CEntry will use it to
3111 // set the current context on the isolate.
3112 __ LoadSmiLiteral(cp, Smi::zero());
3113 __ CallRuntime(Runtime::kWasmDebugBreak, 0);
3114
3115 // Restore registers.
3116 __ MultiPopF64AndV128(WasmDebugBreakFrameConstants::kPushedFpRegs,
3117 WasmDebugBreakFrameConstants::kPushedSimd128Regs, ip,
3118 r0);
3119 __ MultiPop(WasmDebugBreakFrameConstants::kPushedGpRegs);
3120 }
3121 __ Ret();
3122}

3125// Check that the stack was in the old state (if generated code assertions are
3126// enabled), and switch to the new state.
3127void SwitchStackState(MacroAssembler* masm, Register jmpbuf, Register tmp,
3128 wasm::JumpBuffer::StackState old_state,
3129 wasm::JumpBuffer::StackState new_state) {
3130 __ LoadU32(tmp, MemOperand(jmpbuf, wasm::kJmpBufStateOffset));
3131 Label ok;
3132 __ JumpIfEqual(tmp, old_state, &ok);
3133 __ Trap();
3134 __ bind(&ok);
3135 __ mov(tmp, Operand(new_state));
3136 __ StoreU32(tmp, MemOperand(jmpbuf, wasm::kJmpBufStateOffset), r0);
3137}

3139// Switch the stack pointer.
3140void SwitchStackPointer(MacroAssembler* masm, Register jmpbuf) {
3141 __ LoadU64(sp, MemOperand(jmpbuf, wasm::kJmpBufSpOffset));
3142}
3143
3144void FillJumpBuffer(MacroAssembler* masm, Register jmpbuf, Label* target,
3145 Register tmp) {
3146 __ mr(tmp, sp);
3147 __ StoreU64(tmp, MemOperand(jmpbuf, wasm::kJmpBufSpOffset));
3148 __ StoreU64(fp, MemOperand(jmpbuf, wasm::kJmpBufFpOffset));
3149 __ LoadStackLimit(tmp, StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit, r0);
3150 __ StoreU64(tmp, MemOperand(jmpbuf, wasm::kJmpBufStackLimitOffset));
3151
3152 __ GetLabelAddress(tmp, target);
3153 // Stash the address in the jump buffer.
3154 __ StoreU64(tmp, MemOperand(jmpbuf, wasm::kJmpBufPcOffset));
3155}
3156
3157void LoadJumpBuffer(MacroAssembler* masm, Register jmpbuf, bool load_pc,
3158 Register tmp, wasm::JumpBuffer::StackState expected_state) {
3159 SwitchStackPointer(masm, jmpbuf);
3160 __ LoadU64(fp, MemOperand(jmpbuf, wasm::kJmpBufFpOffset));
3161 SwitchStackState(masm, jmpbuf, tmp, expected_state, wasm::JumpBuffer::Active);
3162 if (load_pc) {
3163 __ LoadU64(tmp, MemOperand(jmpbuf, wasm::kJmpBufPcOffset));
3164 __ Jump(tmp);
3165 }
3166 // The stack limit in StackGuard is set separately under the ExecutionAccess
3167 // lock.
3168}

3170void SaveState(MacroAssembler* masm, Register active_continuation, Register tmp,
3171 Label* suspend) {
3172 Register jmpbuf = tmp;
3173 __ LoadU64(jmpbuf,
3174 FieldMemOperand(active_continuation,
3175 WasmContinuationObject::kJmpbufOffset),
3176 r0);
3177
3178 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm);
3179 FillJumpBuffer(masm, jmpbuf, suspend, temps.Acquire());
3180}

3182void LoadTargetJumpBuffer(MacroAssembler* masm, Register target_continuation,
3183 Register tmp,
3184 wasm::JumpBuffer::StackState expected_state) {
3185 Register target_jmpbuf = target_continuation;
3186 __ LoadU64(target_jmpbuf,
3187 FieldMemOperand(target_continuation,
3188 WasmContinuationObject::kJmpbufOffset),
3189 r0);
3190
3191 __ Zero(MemOperand(fp, StackSwitchFrameConstants::kGCScanSlotCountOffset));
3192 // Switch stack!
3193 LoadJumpBuffer(masm, target_jmpbuf, false, tmp, expected_state);
3194}

3196// Updates the stack limit to match the new active stack.
3197// Pass the {finished_continuation} argument to indicate that the stack that we
3198// are switching from returned, and in this case return its memory to the stack
3199// pool.
3200void SwitchStacks(MacroAssembler* masm, Register finished_continuation,
3201 const Register& keep1, const Register& keep2 = no_reg,
3202 const Register& keep3 = no_reg) {
3203 using ER = ExternalReference;
3204
3205 __ Push(keep1);
3206 if (keep2 != no_reg) {
3207 __ Push(keep2);
3208 }
3209 if (keep3 != no_reg) {
3210 __ Push(keep3);
3211 }
3212
3213 if (finished_continuation != no_reg) {
3214 __ PrepareCallCFunction(2, r0);
3215 FrameScope scope(masm, StackFrame::MANUAL);
3216 __ Move(kCArgRegs[0], ExternalReference::isolate_address(masm->isolate()));
3217 __ Move(kCArgRegs[1], finished_continuation);
3218 __ CallCFunction(ER::wasm_return_switch(), 2);
3219 } else {
3220 __ PrepareCallCFunction(1, r0);
3221 FrameScope scope(masm, StackFrame::MANUAL);
3222 __ Move(kCArgRegs[0], ER::isolate_address());
3223 __ CallCFunction(ER::wasm_sync_stack_limit(), 1);
3224 }
3225
3226 if (keep3 != no_reg) {
3227 __ Pop(keep3);
3228 }
3229 if (keep2 != no_reg) {
3230 __ Pop(keep2);
3231 }
3232 __ Pop(keep1);
3233}

3235void ReloadParentContinuation(MacroAssembler* masm, Register return_reg,
3236 Register return_value, Register context,
3237 Register tmp1, Register tmp2, Register tmp3) {
3238 Register active_continuation = tmp1;
3239 __ LoadRoot(active_continuation, RootIndex::kActiveContinuation);
3240
3241 // Set a null pointer in the jump buffer's SP slot to indicate to the stack
3242 // frame iterator that this stack is empty.
3243 Register jmpbuf = tmp2;
3244 __ LoadU64(jmpbuf,
3245 FieldMemOperand(active_continuation,
3246 WasmContinuationObject::kJmpbufOffset),
3247 r0);
3248 __ Zero(MemOperand(jmpbuf, wasm::kJmpBufSpOffset));
3249 {
3250 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm);
3251 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
3252 SwitchStackState(masm, jmpbuf, scratch, wasm::JumpBuffer::Active,
3253 wasm::JumpBuffer::Retired);
3254 }
3255 Register parent = tmp2;
3256 __ LoadTaggedField(parent,
3257 FieldMemOperand(active_continuation,
3258 WasmContinuationObject::kParentOffset),
3259 r0);
3260
3261 // Update active continuation root.
3262 int32_t active_continuation_offset =
3263 MacroAssembler::RootRegisterOffsetForRootIndex(
3264 RootIndex::kActiveContinuation);
3265 __ StoreU64(parent, MemOperand(kRootRegister, active_continuation_offset));
3266 jmpbuf = parent;
3267 __ LoadU64(jmpbuf,
3268 FieldMemOperand(parent, WasmContinuationObject::kJmpbufOffset),
3269 r0);
3270
3271 // Switch stack!
3272 LoadJumpBuffer(masm, jmpbuf, false, tmp3, wasm::JumpBuffer::Inactive);
3273
3274 SwitchStacks(masm, active_continuation, return_reg, return_value, context);
3275}

3277void RestoreParentSuspender(MacroAssembler* masm, Register tmp1,
3278 Register tmp2) {
3279 Register suspender = tmp1;
3280 __ LoadRoot(suspender, RootIndex::kActiveSuspender);
3281 MemOperand state_loc =
3282 FieldMemOperand(suspender, WasmSuspenderObject::kStateOffset);
3283 __ Move(tmp2, Smi::FromInt(WasmSuspenderObject::kInactive));
3284 __ StoreTaggedField(tmp2, state_loc, r0);
3285 __ LoadTaggedField(
3286 suspender, FieldMemOperand(suspender, WasmSuspenderObject::kParentOffset),
3287 r0);
3288
3289 Label undefined;
3290 __ JumpIfRoot(suspender, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue, &undefined);
3291
3292 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
3293 // Check that the parent suspender is active.
3294 Label parent_inactive;
3295 Register state = tmp2;
3296 __ LoadTaggedSignedField(state, state_loc, r0);
3297 __ SmiUntag(state);
3298 __ JumpIfEqual(state, WasmSuspenderObject::kActive, &parent_inactive);
3299 __ Trap();
3300 __ bind(&parent_inactive);
3301 }
3302 __ Move(tmp2, Smi::FromInt(WasmSuspenderObject::kActive));
3303 __ StoreTaggedField(tmp2, state_loc, r0);
3304 __ bind(&undefined);
3305 int32_t active_suspender_offset =
3306 MacroAssembler::RootRegisterOffsetForRootIndex(
3307 RootIndex::kActiveSuspender);
3308 __ StoreU64(suspender, MemOperand(kRootRegister, active_suspender_offset));
3309}

3316class RegisterAllocator {
3317 public:
3318 class Scoped {
3319 public:
3320 Scoped(RegisterAllocator* allocator, Register* reg)
3321 : allocator_(allocator), reg_(reg) {}
3322 ~Scoped() { allocator_->Free(reg_); }
3323
3324 private:
3325 RegisterAllocator* allocator_;
3326 Register* reg_;
3327 };
3328
3329 explicit RegisterAllocator(const RegList& registers)
3330 : initial_(registers), available_(registers) {}
3331 void Ask(Register* reg) {
3332 DCHECK_EQ(*reg, no_reg);
3333 DCHECK(!available_.is_empty());
3334 *reg = available_.PopFirst();
3335 allocated_registers_.push_back(reg);
3336 }
3337
3338 bool registerIsAvailable(const Register& reg) { return available_.has(reg); }
3339
3340 void Pinned(const Register& requested, Register* reg) {
3341 DCHECK(registerIsAvailable(requested));
3342 *reg = requested;
3343 Reserve(requested);
3344 allocated_registers_.push_back(reg);
3345 }
3346
3347 void Free(Register* reg) {
3348 DCHECK_NE(*reg, no_reg);
3349 available_.set(*reg);
3350 *reg = no_reg;
3351 allocated_registers_.erase(
3352 find(allocated_registers_.begin(), allocated_registers_.end(), reg));
3353 }
3354
3355 void Reserve(const Register& reg) {
3356 if (reg == no_reg) {
3357 return;
3358 }
3359 DCHECK(registerIsAvailable(reg));
3360 available_.clear(reg);
3361 }
3362
3363 void Reserve(const Register& reg1, const Register& reg2,
3364 const Register& reg3 = no_reg, const Register& reg4 = no_reg,
3365 const Register& reg5 = no_reg, const Register& reg6 = no_reg) {
3366 Reserve(reg1);
3367 Reserve(reg2);
3368 Reserve(reg3);
3369 Reserve(reg4);
3370 Reserve(reg5);
3371 Reserve(reg6);
3372 }
3373
3374 bool IsUsed(const Register& reg) {
3375 return initial_.has(reg) && !registerIsAvailable(reg);
3376 }
3377
3378 void ResetExcept(const Register& reg1 = no_reg, const Register& reg2 = no_reg,
3379 const Register& reg3 = no_reg, const Register& reg4 = no_reg,
3380 const Register& reg5 = no_reg,
3381 const Register& reg6 = no_reg) {
3382 available_ = initial_;
3383 available_.clear(reg1);
3384 available_.clear(reg2);
3385 available_.clear(reg3);
3386 available_.clear(reg4);
3387 available_.clear(reg5);
3388 available_.clear(reg6);
3389
3390 auto it = allocated_registers_.begin();
3391 while (it != allocated_registers_.end()) {
3392 if (registerIsAvailable(**it)) {
3393 **it = no_reg;
3394 it = allocated_registers_.erase(it);
3395 } else {
3396 it++;
3397 }
3398 }
3399 }
3400
3401 static RegisterAllocator WithAllocatableGeneralRegisters() {
3402 RegList list;
3403 const RegisterConfiguration* config(RegisterConfiguration::Default());
3404
3405 for (int i = 0; i < config->num_allocatable_general_registers(); ++i) {
3406 int code = config->GetAllocatableGeneralCode(i);
3407 Register candidate = Register::from_code(code);
3408 list.set(candidate);
3409 }
3410 return RegisterAllocator(list);
3411 }
3412
3413 private:
3414 std::vector<Register*> allocated_registers_;
3415 const RegList initial_;
3416 RegList available_;
3417};

3420 Register Name = no_reg; \
3421 regs.Ask(&Name);
3422
3423#define DEFINE_REG_W(Name) \
3424 DEFINE_REG(Name); \
3425 Name = Name.W();
3426
3427#define ASSIGN_REG(Name) regs.Ask(&Name);
3428
3429#define ASSIGN_REG_W(Name) \
3430 ASSIGN_REG(Name); \
3431 Name = Name.W();
3432
3433#define DEFINE_PINNED(Name, Reg) \
3434 Register Name = no_reg; \
3435 regs.Pinned(Reg, &Name);
3436
3437#define ASSIGN_PINNED(Name, Reg) regs.Pinned(Reg, &Name);
3438
3439#define DEFINE_SCOPED(Name) \
3440 DEFINE_REG(Name) \
3441 RegisterAllocator::Scoped scope_##Name(&regs, &Name);
3442

3445// Loads the context field of the WasmTrustedInstanceData or WasmImportData
3446// depending on the data's type, and places the result in the input register.
3447void GetContextFromImplicitArg(MacroAssembler* masm, Register data,
3448 Register scratch) {
3449 __ LoadTaggedField(scratch, FieldMemOperand(data, HeapObject::kMapOffset),
3450 r0);
3451 __ CompareInstanceType(scratch, scratch, WASM_TRUSTED_INSTANCE_DATA_TYPE);
3452 Label instance;
3453 Label end;
3454 __ beq(&instance);
3455 __ LoadTaggedField(
3456 data, FieldMemOperand(data, WasmImportData::kNativeContextOffset), r0);
3457 __ jmp(&end);
3458 __ bind(&instance);
3459 __ LoadTaggedField(
3460 data,
3461 FieldMemOperand(data, WasmTrustedInstanceData::kNativeContextOffset), r0);
3462 __ bind(&end);
3463}

3467void Builtins::Generate_WasmToJsWrapperAsm(MacroAssembler* masm) {
3468 // Push registers in reverse order so that they are on the stack like
3469 // in an array, with the first item being at the lowest address.
3470 DoubleRegList fp_regs;
3471 for (DoubleRegister fp_param_reg : wasm::kFpParamRegisters) {
3472 fp_regs.set(fp_param_reg);
3473 }
3474 __ MultiPushDoubles(fp_regs);
3475
3476 // Push the GP registers in reverse order so that they are on the stack like
3477 // in an array, with the first item being at the lowest address.
3478 RegList gp_regs;
3479 for (size_t i = arraysize(wasm::kGpParamRegisters) - 1; i > 0; --i) {
3480 gp_regs.set(wasm::kGpParamRegisters[i]);
3481 }
3482 __ MultiPush(gp_regs);
3483 // Reserve a slot for the signature.
3484 __ Push(r3);
3485 __ TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmToJsWrapperCSA);
3486}

3491
3492void Builtins::Generate_WasmSuspend(MacroAssembler* masm) {
3493 auto regs = RegisterAllocator::WithAllocatableGeneralRegisters();
3494 // Set up the stackframe.
3495 __ EnterFrame(StackFrame::STACK_SWITCH);
3496
3497 DEFINE_PINNED(suspender, r3);
3498 DEFINE_PINNED(context, kContextRegister);
3499
3500 __ SubS64(
3501 sp, sp,
3502 Operand(StackSwitchFrameConstants::kNumSpillSlots * kSystemPointerSize));
3503 // Set a sentinel value for the spill slots visited by the GC.
3504 ResetStackSwitchFrameStackSlots(masm);
3505
3506 // -------------------------------------------
3507 // Save current state in active jump buffer.
3508 // -------------------------------------------
3509 Label resume;
3510 DEFINE_REG(continuation);
3511 __ LoadRoot(continuation, RootIndex::kActiveContinuation);
3512 DEFINE_REG(jmpbuf);
3513 DEFINE_REG(scratch);
3514 __ LoadU64(
3515 jmpbuf,
3516 FieldMemOperand(continuation, WasmContinuationObject::kJmpbufOffset), r0);
3517 FillJumpBuffer(masm, jmpbuf, &resume, scratch);
3518 SwitchStackState(masm, jmpbuf, scratch, wasm::JumpBuffer::Active,
3519 wasm::JumpBuffer::Suspended);
3520 __ Move(scratch, Smi::FromInt(WasmSuspenderObject::kSuspended));
3521 __ StoreTaggedField(
3522 scratch, FieldMemOperand(suspender, WasmSuspenderObject::kStateOffset),
3523 r0);
3524 regs.ResetExcept(suspender, continuation);
3525
3526 DEFINE_REG(suspender_continuation);
3527 __ LoadTaggedField(
3528 suspender_continuation,
3529 FieldMemOperand(suspender, WasmSuspenderObject::kContinuationOffset), r0);
3530 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
3531 // -------------------------------------------
3532 // Check that the suspender's continuation is the active continuation.
3533 // -------------------------------------------
3534 // TODO(thibaudm): Once we add core stack-switching instructions, this
3535 // check will not hold anymore: it's possible that the active continuation
3536 // changed (due to an internal switch), so we have to update the suspender.
3537 __ CmpS64(suspender_continuation, continuation);
3538 Label ok;
3539 __ beq(&ok);
3540 __ Trap();
3541 __ bind(&ok);
3542 }
3543 FREE_REG(continuation);
3544 // -------------------------------------------
3545 // Update roots.
3546 // -------------------------------------------
3547 DEFINE_REG(caller);
3548 __ LoadTaggedField(caller,
3549 FieldMemOperand(suspender_continuation,
3550 WasmContinuationObject::kParentOffset),
3551 r0);
3552 int32_t active_continuation_offset =
3553 MacroAssembler::RootRegisterOffsetForRootIndex(
3554 RootIndex::kActiveContinuation);
3555 __ StoreU64(caller, MemOperand(kRootRegister, active_continuation_offset));
3556 DEFINE_REG(parent);
3557 __ LoadTaggedField(
3558 parent, FieldMemOperand(suspender, WasmSuspenderObject::kParentOffset),
3559 r0);
3560 int32_t active_suspender_offset =
3561 MacroAssembler::RootRegisterOffsetForRootIndex(
3562 RootIndex::kActiveSuspender);
3563 __ StoreU64(parent, MemOperand(kRootRegister, active_suspender_offset));
3564 regs.ResetExcept(suspender, caller);
3565
3566 // -------------------------------------------
3567 // Load jump buffer.
3568 // -------------------------------------------
3569 SwitchStacks(masm, no_reg, caller, suspender);
3570 ASSIGN_REG(jmpbuf);
3571 __ LoadU64(jmpbuf,
3572 FieldMemOperand(caller, WasmContinuationObject::kJmpbufOffset),
3573 r0);
3574 __ LoadTaggedField(
3575 kReturnRegister0,
3576 FieldMemOperand(suspender, WasmSuspenderObject::kPromiseOffset), r0);
3577 MemOperand GCScanSlotPlace =
3578 MemOperand(fp, StackSwitchFrameConstants::kGCScanSlotCountOffset);
3579 __ Zero(GCScanSlotPlace);
3580 ASSIGN_REG(scratch)
3581 LoadJumpBuffer(masm, jmpbuf, true, scratch, wasm::JumpBuffer::Inactive);
3582 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
3583 __ Trap();
3584 }
3585 __ bind(&resume);
3586 __ LeaveFrame(StackFrame::STACK_SWITCH);
3587 __ blr();
3588}

3590namespace {
3591// Resume the suspender stored in the closure. We generate two variants of this
3592// builtin: the onFulfilled variant resumes execution at the saved PC and
3593// forwards the value, the onRejected variant throws the value.
3594
3595void Generate_WasmResumeHelper(MacroAssembler* masm, wasm::OnResume on_resume) {
3596 auto regs = RegisterAllocator::WithAllocatableGeneralRegisters();
3597 __ EnterFrame(StackFrame::STACK_SWITCH);
3598
3599 DEFINE_PINNED(closure, kJSFunctionRegister); // r4
3600
3601 __ SubS64(
3602 sp, sp,
3603 Operand(StackSwitchFrameConstants::kNumSpillSlots * kSystemPointerSize));
3604 // Set a sentinel value for the spill slots visited by the GC.
3605 ResetStackSwitchFrameStackSlots(masm);
3606
3607 regs.ResetExcept(closure);
3608
3609 // -------------------------------------------
3610 // Load suspender from closure.
3611 // -------------------------------------------
3612 DEFINE_REG(sfi);
3613 __ LoadTaggedField(
3614 sfi,
3615 MemOperand(
3616 closure,
3617 wasm::ObjectAccess::SharedFunctionInfoOffsetInTaggedJSFunction()),
3618 r0);
3619 FREE_REG(closure);
3620 // Suspender should be ObjectRegister register to be used in
3621 // RecordWriteField calls later.
3622 DEFINE_PINNED(suspender, WriteBarrierDescriptor::ObjectRegister());
3623 DEFINE_REG(resume_data);
3624 __ LoadTaggedField(
3625 resume_data,
3626 FieldMemOperand(sfi, SharedFunctionInfo::kUntrustedFunctionDataOffset),
3627 r0);
3628 __ LoadTaggedField(
3629 suspender, FieldMemOperand(resume_data, WasmResumeData::kSuspenderOffset),
3630 r0);
3631 // Check the suspender state.
3632 Label suspender_is_suspended;
3633 DEFINE_REG(state);
3634 __ LoadTaggedSignedField(
3635 state, FieldMemOperand(suspender, WasmSuspenderObject::kStateOffset), r0);
3636 __ SmiUntag(state);
3637 __ JumpIfEqual(state, WasmSuspenderObject::kSuspended,
3638 &suspender_is_suspended);
3639 __ Trap();
3640
3641 regs.ResetExcept(suspender);
3642
3643 __ bind(&suspender_is_suspended);
3644 // -------------------------------------------
3645 // Save current state.
3646 // -------------------------------------------
3647 Label suspend;
3648 DEFINE_REG(active_continuation);
3649 __ LoadRoot(active_continuation, RootIndex::kActiveContinuation);
3650 DEFINE_REG(current_jmpbuf);
3651 DEFINE_REG(scratch);
3652 __ LoadU64(current_jmpbuf,
3653 FieldMemOperand(active_continuation,
3654 WasmContinuationObject::kJmpbufOffset),
3655 r0);
3656 FillJumpBuffer(masm, current_jmpbuf, &suspend, scratch);
3657 SwitchStackState(masm, current_jmpbuf, scratch, wasm::JumpBuffer::Active,
3658 wasm::JumpBuffer::Inactive);
3659 FREE_REG(current_jmpbuf);
3660
3661 // -------------------------------------------
3662 // Set the suspender and continuation parents and update the roots
3663 // -------------------------------------------
3664 DEFINE_REG(active_suspender);
3665 __ LoadRoot(active_suspender, RootIndex::kActiveSuspender);
3666 __ StoreTaggedField(
3667 active_suspender,
3668 FieldMemOperand(suspender, WasmSuspenderObject::kParentOffset), r0);
3669 __ RecordWriteField(suspender, WasmSuspenderObject::kParentOffset,
3670 active_suspender, ip, kLRHasBeenSaved,
3671 SaveFPRegsMode::kIgnore);
3672 __ Move(scratch, Smi::FromInt(WasmSuspenderObject::kActive));
3673 __ StoreTaggedField(
3674 scratch, FieldMemOperand(suspender, WasmSuspenderObject::kStateOffset),
3675 r0);
3676 int32_t active_suspender_offset =
3677 MacroAssembler::RootRegisterOffsetForRootIndex(
3678 RootIndex::kActiveSuspender);
3679 __ StoreU64(suspender, MemOperand(kRootRegister, active_suspender_offset));
3680
3681 // Next line we are going to load a field from suspender, but we have to use
3682 // the same register for target_continuation to use it in RecordWriteField.
3683 // So, free suspender here to use pinned reg, but load from it next line.
3684 FREE_REG(suspender);
3685 DEFINE_PINNED(target_continuation, WriteBarrierDescriptor::ObjectRegister());
3686 suspender = target_continuation;
3687 __ LoadTaggedField(
3688 target_continuation,
3689 FieldMemOperand(suspender, WasmSuspenderObject::kContinuationOffset), r0);
3690 suspender = no_reg;
3691
3692 __ StoreTaggedField(active_continuation,
3693 FieldMemOperand(target_continuation,
3694 WasmContinuationObject::kParentOffset),
3695 r0);
3696 __ RecordWriteField(
3697 target_continuation, WasmContinuationObject::kParentOffset,
3698 active_continuation, ip, kLRHasBeenSaved, SaveFPRegsMode::kIgnore);
3699 FREE_REG(active_continuation);
3700 int32_t active_continuation_offset =
3701 MacroAssembler::RootRegisterOffsetForRootIndex(
3702 RootIndex::kActiveContinuation);
3703 __ StoreU64(target_continuation,
3704 MemOperand(kRootRegister, active_continuation_offset));
3705
3706 SwitchStacks(masm, no_reg, target_continuation);
3707
3708 regs.ResetExcept(target_continuation);
3709
3710 // -------------------------------------------
3711 // Load state from target jmpbuf (longjmp).
3712 // -------------------------------------------
3713 regs.Reserve(kReturnRegister0);
3714 DEFINE_REG(target_jmpbuf);
3715 ASSIGN_REG(scratch);
3716 __ LoadU64(target_jmpbuf,
3717 FieldMemOperand(target_continuation,
3718 WasmContinuationObject::kJmpbufOffset),
3719 r0);
3720 // Move resolved value to return register.
3721 __ LoadU64(kReturnRegister0, MemOperand(fp, 3 * kSystemPointerSize));
3722 MemOperand GCScanSlotPlace =
3723 MemOperand(fp, StackSwitchFrameConstants::kGCScanSlotCountOffset);
3724 __ Zero(GCScanSlotPlace);
3725 if (on_resume == wasm::OnResume::kThrow) {
3726 // Switch to the continuation's stack without restoring the PC.
3727 LoadJumpBuffer(masm, target_jmpbuf, false, scratch,
3728 wasm::JumpBuffer::Suspended);
3729 // Pop this frame now. The unwinder expects that the first STACK_SWITCH
3730 // frame is the outermost one.
3731 __ LeaveFrame(StackFrame::STACK_SWITCH);
3732 // Forward the onRejected value to kThrow.
3733 __ Push(kReturnRegister0);
3734 __ CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrow);
3735 } else {
3736 // Resume the continuation normally.
3737 LoadJumpBuffer(masm, target_jmpbuf, true, scratch,
3738 wasm::JumpBuffer::Suspended);
3739 }
3740 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
3741 __ Trap();
3742 }
3743 __ bind(&suspend);
3744 __ LeaveFrame(StackFrame::STACK_SWITCH);
3745 // Pop receiver + parameter.
3746 __ AddS64(sp, sp, Operand(2 * kSystemPointerSize));
3747 __ blr();
3748}
3749} // namespace

3764namespace {
3765void SwitchToAllocatedStack(MacroAssembler* masm, RegisterAllocator& regs,
3766 Register wasm_instance, Register wrapper_buffer,
3767 Register& original_fp, Register& new_wrapper_buffer,
3768 Label* suspend) {
3769 ResetStackSwitchFrameStackSlots(masm);
3770 DEFINE_SCOPED(scratch)
3771 DEFINE_REG(target_continuation)
3772 __ LoadRoot(target_continuation, RootIndex::kActiveContinuation);
3773 DEFINE_REG(parent_continuation)
3774 __ LoadTaggedField(parent_continuation,
3775 FieldMemOperand(target_continuation,
3776 WasmContinuationObject::kParentOffset),
3777 r0);
3778
3779 SaveState(masm, parent_continuation, scratch, suspend);
3780
3781 SwitchStacks(masm, no_reg, wasm_instance, wrapper_buffer);
3782
3783 FREE_REG(parent_continuation);
3784 // Save the old stack's fp in r15, and use it to access the parameters in
3785 // the parent frame.
3786 regs.Pinned(r15, &original_fp);
3787 __ Move(original_fp, fp);
3788 __ LoadRoot(target_continuation, RootIndex::kActiveContinuation);
3789 LoadTargetJumpBuffer(masm, target_continuation, scratch,
3790 wasm::JumpBuffer::Suspended);
3791 FREE_REG(target_continuation);
3792
3793 // Push the loaded fp. We know it is null, because there is no frame yet,
3794 // so we could also push 0 directly. In any case we need to push it,
3795 // because this marks the base of the stack segment for
3796 // the stack frame iterator.
3797 __ EnterFrame(StackFrame::STACK_SWITCH);
3798
3799 int stack_space =
3800 RoundUp(StackSwitchFrameConstants::kNumSpillSlots * kSystemPointerSize +
3801 JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferSize,
3802 16);
3803 __ SubS64(sp, sp, Operand(stack_space));
3804 __ EnforceStackAlignment();
3805
3806 ASSIGN_REG(new_wrapper_buffer)
3807
3808 __ Move(new_wrapper_buffer, sp);
3809 // Copy data needed for return handling from old wrapper buffer to new one.
3810
3811 __ LoadU64(
3812 scratch,
3813 MemOperand(wrapper_buffer,
3814 JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferReturnCount));
3815 __ StoreU64(
3816 scratch,
3817 MemOperand(new_wrapper_buffer,
3818 JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferReturnCount));
3819 __ LoadU64(
3820 scratch,
3821 MemOperand(wrapper_buffer,
3822 JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferRefReturnCount));
3823 __ StoreU64(
3824 scratch,
3825 MemOperand(new_wrapper_buffer,
3826 JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferRefReturnCount));
3827 __ LoadU64(
3828 scratch,
3829 MemOperand(
3830 wrapper_buffer,
3831 JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferSigRepresentationArray));
3832 __ StoreU64(
3833 scratch,
3834 MemOperand(
3835 new_wrapper_buffer,
3836 JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferSigRepresentationArray));
3837
3838 __ LoadU64(
3839 scratch,
3840 MemOperand(
3841 wrapper_buffer,
3842 JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferSigRepresentationArray +
3843 4));
3844 __ StoreU64(
3845 scratch,
3846 MemOperand(
3847 new_wrapper_buffer,
3848 JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferSigRepresentationArray +
3849 4));
3850}
3851
3852void SwitchBackAndReturnPromise(MacroAssembler* masm, RegisterAllocator& regs,
3853 wasm::Promise mode, Label* return_promise) {
3854 regs.ResetExcept();
3855 // The return value of the wasm function becomes the parameter of the
3856 // FulfillPromise builtin, and the promise is the return value of this
3857 // wrapper.
3858 static const Builtin_FulfillPromise_InterfaceDescriptor desc;
3859 DEFINE_PINNED(promise, desc.GetRegisterParameter(0));
3860 DEFINE_PINNED(return_value, desc.GetRegisterParameter(1));
3861 DEFINE_SCOPED(tmp);
3862 DEFINE_SCOPED(tmp2);
3863 DEFINE_SCOPED(tmp3);
3864 if (mode == wasm::kPromise) {
3865 __ Move(return_value, kReturnRegister0);
3866 __ LoadRoot(promise, RootIndex::kActiveSuspender);
3867 __ LoadTaggedField(
3868 promise, FieldMemOperand(promise, WasmSuspenderObject::kPromiseOffset),
3869 r0);
3870 }
3871
3872 __ LoadU64(kContextRegister,
3873 MemOperand(fp, StackSwitchFrameConstants::kImplicitArgOffset));
3874 GetContextFromImplicitArg(masm, kContextRegister, tmp);
3875
3876 ReloadParentContinuation(masm, promise, return_value, kContextRegister, tmp,
3877 tmp2, tmp3);
3878 RestoreParentSuspender(masm, tmp, tmp2);
3879
3880 if (mode == wasm::kPromise) {
3881 __ mov(tmp, Operand(1));
3882 __ StoreU64(
3883 tmp, MemOperand(fp, StackSwitchFrameConstants::kGCScanSlotCountOffset));
3884 __ Push(promise);
3885 __ CallBuiltin(Builtin::kFulfillPromise);
3886 __ Pop(promise);
3887 }
3888 FREE_REG(promise);
3889 FREE_REG(return_value);
3890 __ bind(return_promise);
3891}
3892
3893void GenerateExceptionHandlingLandingPad(MacroAssembler* masm,
3894 RegisterAllocator& regs,
3895 Label* return_promise) {
3896 regs.ResetExcept();
3897 static const Builtin_RejectPromise_InterfaceDescriptor desc;
3898 DEFINE_PINNED(promise, desc.GetRegisterParameter(0));
3899 DEFINE_PINNED(reason, desc.GetRegisterParameter(1));
3900 DEFINE_PINNED(debug_event, desc.GetRegisterParameter(2));
3901 int catch_handler = __ pc_offset();
3902
3903 DEFINE_SCOPED(thread_in_wasm_flag_addr);
3904 thread_in_wasm_flag_addr = r5;
3905
3906 // Unset thread_in_wasm_flag.
3907 __ LoadU64(
3908 thread_in_wasm_flag_addr,
3909 MemOperand(kRootRegister, Isolate::thread_in_wasm_flag_address_offset()));
3910 __ mov(r0, Operand(0));
3911 __ StoreU32(r0, MemOperand(thread_in_wasm_flag_addr, 0), no_reg);
3912
3913 // The exception becomes the parameter of the RejectPromise builtin, and the
3914 // promise is the return value of this wrapper.
3915 __ Move(reason, kReturnRegister0);
3916 __ LoadRoot(promise, RootIndex::kActiveSuspender);
3917 __ LoadTaggedField(
3918 promise, FieldMemOperand(promise, WasmSuspenderObject::kPromiseOffset),
3919 r0);
3920
3921 DEFINE_SCOPED(tmp);
3922 DEFINE_SCOPED(tmp2);
3923 DEFINE_SCOPED(tmp3);
3924 __ LoadU64(kContextRegister,
3925 MemOperand(fp, StackSwitchFrameConstants::kImplicitArgOffset));
3926 GetContextFromImplicitArg(masm, kContextRegister, tmp);
3927 ReloadParentContinuation(masm, promise, reason, kContextRegister, tmp, tmp2,
3928 tmp3);
3929 RestoreParentSuspender(masm, tmp, tmp2);
3930
3931 __ mov(tmp, Operand(1));
3932 __ StoreU64(
3933 tmp, MemOperand(fp, StackSwitchFrameConstants::kGCScanSlotCountOffset));
3934 __ Push(promise);
3935 __ LoadRoot(debug_event, RootIndex::kTrueValue);
3936 __ CallBuiltin(Builtin::kRejectPromise);
3937 __ Pop(promise);
3938
3939 // Run the rest of the wrapper normally (deconstruct the frame, ...).
3940 __ b(return_promise);
3941
3942 masm->isolate()->builtins()->SetJSPIPromptHandlerOffset(catch_handler);
3943}
3944
3945void JSToWasmWrapperHelper(MacroAssembler* masm, wasm::Promise mode) {
3946 bool stack_switch = mode == wasm::kPromise || mode == wasm::kStressSwitch;
3947 auto regs = RegisterAllocator::WithAllocatableGeneralRegisters();
3948
3949 __ EnterFrame(stack_switch ? StackFrame::STACK_SWITCH
3950 : StackFrame::JS_TO_WASM);
3951
3952 __ AllocateStackSpace(StackSwitchFrameConstants::kNumSpillSlots *
3953 kSystemPointerSize);
3954
3955 // Load the implicit argument (instance data or import data) from the frame.
3956 DEFINE_PINNED(implicit_arg, kWasmImplicitArgRegister);
3957 __ LoadU64(implicit_arg,
3958 MemOperand(fp, JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kImplicitArgOffset));
3959
3960 DEFINE_PINNED(wrapper_buffer,
3961 WasmJSToWasmWrapperDescriptor::WrapperBufferRegister());
3962
3963 Label suspend;
3964 Register original_fp = no_reg;
3965 Register new_wrapper_buffer = no_reg;
3966 if (stack_switch) {
3967 SwitchToAllocatedStack(masm, regs, implicit_arg, wrapper_buffer,
3968 original_fp, new_wrapper_buffer, &suspend);
3969 } else {
3970 original_fp = fp;
3971 new_wrapper_buffer = wrapper_buffer;
3972 }
3973
3974 regs.ResetExcept(original_fp, wrapper_buffer, implicit_arg,
3975 new_wrapper_buffer);
3976
3977 {
3978 __ StoreU64(
3979 new_wrapper_buffer,
3980 MemOperand(fp, JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferOffset));
3981 if (stack_switch) {
3982 __ StoreU64(
3983 implicit_arg,
3984 MemOperand(fp, StackSwitchFrameConstants::kImplicitArgOffset));
3985 DEFINE_SCOPED(scratch)
3986 __ LoadU64(
3987 scratch,
3988 MemOperand(original_fp,
3989 JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kResultArrayParamOffset));
3990 __ StoreU64(
3991 scratch,
3992 MemOperand(fp, StackSwitchFrameConstants::kResultArrayOffset));
3993 }
3994 }
3995 {
3996 DEFINE_SCOPED(result_size);
3997 __ LoadU64(
3998 result_size,
3999 MemOperand(wrapper_buffer, JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::
4000 kWrapperBufferStackReturnBufferSize));
4001 __ ShiftLeftU64(r0, result_size, Operand(kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
4002 __ SubS64(sp, sp, r0);
4003 }
4004
4005 __ StoreU64(
4006 sp,
4007 MemOperand(
4008 new_wrapper_buffer,
4009 JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferStackReturnBufferStart));
4010
4011 if (stack_switch) {
4012 FREE_REG(new_wrapper_buffer)
4013 }
4014 FREE_REG(implicit_arg)
4015 for (auto reg : wasm::kGpParamRegisters) {
4016 regs.Reserve(reg);
4017 }
4018
4019 // The first GP parameter holds the trusted instance data or the import data.
4020 // This is handled specially.
4021 int stack_params_offset =
4022 (arraysize(wasm::kGpParamRegisters) - 1) * kSystemPointerSize +
4023 arraysize(wasm::kFpParamRegisters) * kDoubleSize;
4024 int param_padding = stack_params_offset & kSystemPointerSize;
4025 stack_params_offset += param_padding;
4026
4027 {
4028 DEFINE_SCOPED(params_start);
4029 __ LoadU64(
4030 params_start,
4031 MemOperand(wrapper_buffer,
4032 JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferParamStart));
4033 {
4034 // Push stack parameters on the stack.
4035 DEFINE_SCOPED(params_end);
4036 __ LoadU64(
4037 params_end,
4038 MemOperand(wrapper_buffer,
4039 JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferParamEnd));
4040 DEFINE_SCOPED(last_stack_param);
4041
4042 __ AddS64(last_stack_param, params_start, Operand(stack_params_offset));
4043 Label loop_start;
4044 __ bind(&loop_start);
4045
4046 Label finish_stack_params;
4047 __ CmpS64(last_stack_param, params_end);
4048 __ bge(&finish_stack_params);
4049
4050 // Push parameter
4051 {
4052 DEFINE_SCOPED(scratch);
4053 __ AddS64(params_end, params_end, Operand(-kSystemPointerSize));
4054 __ LoadU64(r0, MemOperand(params_end), r0);
4055 __ push(r0);
4056 }
4057 __ jmp(&loop_start);
4058
4059 __ bind(&finish_stack_params);
4060 }
4061
4062 size_t next_offset = 0;
4063 for (size_t i = 1; i < arraysize(wasm::kGpParamRegisters); i++) {
4064 // Check that {params_start} does not overlap with any of the parameter
4065 // registers, so that we don't overwrite it by accident with the loads
4066 // below.
4067 DCHECK_NE(params_start, wasm::kGpParamRegisters[i]);
4068 __ LoadU64(wasm::kGpParamRegisters[i],
4069 MemOperand(params_start, next_offset));
4070 next_offset += kSystemPointerSize;
4071 }
4072
4073 next_offset += param_padding;
4074 for (size_t i = 0; i < arraysize(wasm::kFpParamRegisters); i++) {
4075 __ LoadF64(wasm::kFpParamRegisters[i],
4076 MemOperand(params_start, next_offset));
4077 next_offset += kDoubleSize;
4078 }
4079 DCHECK_EQ(next_offset, stack_params_offset);
4080 }
4081
4082 {
4083 DEFINE_SCOPED(thread_in_wasm_flag_addr);
4084 __ LoadU64(thread_in_wasm_flag_addr,
4085 MemOperand(kRootRegister,
4086 Isolate::thread_in_wasm_flag_address_offset()));
4087 DEFINE_SCOPED(scratch);
4088 __ mov(scratch, Operand(1));
4089 __ StoreU32(scratch, MemOperand(thread_in_wasm_flag_addr, 0), no_reg);
4090 }
4091
4092 __ Zero(MemOperand(fp, StackSwitchFrameConstants::kGCScanSlotCountOffset));
4093 {
4094 DEFINE_SCOPED(call_target);
4095 __ LoadWasmCodePointer(
4096 call_target,
4097 MemOperand(wrapper_buffer,
4098 JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferCallTarget));
4099 __ CallWasmCodePointer(call_target);
4100 }
4101
4102 regs.ResetExcept();
4103 // The wrapper_buffer has to be in r5 as the correct parameter register.
4104 regs.Reserve(kReturnRegister0, kReturnRegister1);
4105 ASSIGN_PINNED(wrapper_buffer, r5);
4106 {
4107 DEFINE_SCOPED(thread_in_wasm_flag_addr);
4108 __ LoadU64(thread_in_wasm_flag_addr,
4109 MemOperand(kRootRegister,
4110 Isolate::thread_in_wasm_flag_address_offset()));
4111 __ mov(r0, Operand(0));
4112 __ StoreU32(r0, MemOperand(thread_in_wasm_flag_addr, 0), no_reg);
4113 }
4114
4115 __ LoadU64(
4116 wrapper_buffer,
4117 MemOperand(fp, JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferOffset));
4118
4119 __ StoreF64(
4120 wasm::kFpReturnRegisters[0],
4121 MemOperand(
4122 wrapper_buffer,
4123 JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferFPReturnRegister1));
4124 __ StoreF64(
4125 wasm::kFpReturnRegisters[1],
4126 MemOperand(
4127 wrapper_buffer,
4128 JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferFPReturnRegister2));
4129 __ StoreU64(
4130 wasm::kGpReturnRegisters[0],
4131 MemOperand(
4132 wrapper_buffer,
4133 JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferGPReturnRegister1));
4134 __ StoreU64(
4135 wasm::kGpReturnRegisters[1],
4136 MemOperand(
4137 wrapper_buffer,
4138 JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferGPReturnRegister2));
4139 // Call the return value builtin with
4140 // r3: wasm instance.
4141 // r4: the result JSArray for multi-return.
4142 // r5: pointer to the byte buffer which contains all parameters.
4143 if (stack_switch) {
4144 __ LoadU64(r4,
4145 MemOperand(fp, StackSwitchFrameConstants::kResultArrayOffset));
4146 __ LoadU64(r3,
4147 MemOperand(fp, StackSwitchFrameConstants::kImplicitArgOffset));
4148 } else {
4149 __ LoadU64(
4150 r4,
4151 MemOperand(fp, JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kResultArrayParamOffset));
4152 __ LoadU64(
4153 r3, MemOperand(fp, JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kImplicitArgOffset));
4154 }
4155 Register scratch = r6;
4156 GetContextFromImplicitArg(masm, r3, scratch);
4157
4158 __ CallBuiltin(Builtin::kJSToWasmHandleReturns);
4159
4160 Label return_promise;
4161 if (stack_switch) {
4162 SwitchBackAndReturnPromise(masm, regs, mode, &return_promise);
4163 }
4164 __ bind(&suspend);
4165
4166 __ LeaveFrame(stack_switch ? StackFrame::STACK_SWITCH
4167 : StackFrame::JS_TO_WASM);
4168 // Despite returning to the different location for regular and stack switching
4169 // versions, incoming argument count matches both cases:
4170 // instance and result array without suspend or
4171 // or promise resolve/reject params for callback.
4172 __ AddS64(sp, sp, Operand(2 * kSystemPointerSize));
4173 __ blr();
4174
4175 // Catch handler for the stack-switching wrapper: reject the promise with the
4176 // thrown exception.
4177 if (mode == wasm::kPromise) {
4178 GenerateExceptionHandlingLandingPad(masm, regs, &return_promise);
4179 }
4180}

4197static constexpr Register kOldSPRegister = r16;
4198static constexpr Register kSwitchFlagRegister = r17;
4199
4200void SwitchToTheCentralStackIfNeeded(MacroAssembler* masm, Register argc_input,
4201 Register target_input,
4202 Register argv_input) {
4203 using ER = ExternalReference;
4204
4205 __ Move(kOldSPRegister, sp);
4206
4207 // Using r5 & r6 as temporary registers, because they will be rewritten
4208 // before exiting to native code anyway.
4209
4210 ER on_central_stack_flag_loc = ER::Create(
4211 IsolateAddressId::kIsOnCentralStackFlagAddress, masm->isolate());
4212 __ Move(kSwitchFlagRegister, on_central_stack_flag_loc);
4213 __ LoadU8(kSwitchFlagRegister, MemOperand(kSwitchFlagRegister));
4214
4215 Label do_not_need_to_switch;
4216 __ CmpU32(kSwitchFlagRegister, Operand(0), r0);
4217 __ bne(&do_not_need_to_switch);
4218
4219 // Switch to central stack.
4220
4221 Register central_stack_sp = r5;
4222 DCHECK(!AreAliased(central_stack_sp, argc_input, argv_input, target_input));
4223 {
4224 __ Push(argc_input);
4225 __ Push(target_input);
4226 __ Push(argv_input);
4227 __ PrepareCallCFunction(2, r0);
4228 __ Move(kCArgRegs[0], ER::isolate_address());
4229 __ Move(kCArgRegs[1], kOldSPRegister);
4230 __ CallCFunction(ER::wasm_switch_to_the_central_stack(), 2,
4231 SetIsolateDataSlots::kNo);
4232 __ Move(central_stack_sp, kReturnRegister0);
4233 __ Pop(argv_input);
4234 __ Pop(target_input);
4235 __ Pop(argc_input);
4236 }
4237
4238 static constexpr int kReturnAddressSlotOffset = 1 * kSystemPointerSize;
4239 static constexpr int kPadding = 1 * kSystemPointerSize;
4240 __ SubS64(sp, central_stack_sp, Operand(kReturnAddressSlotOffset + kPadding));
4241 __ EnforceStackAlignment();
4242
4243 // Update the sp saved in the frame.
4244 // It will be used to calculate the callee pc during GC.
4245 // The pc is going to be on the new stack segment, so rewrite it here.
4246 __ AddS64(central_stack_sp, sp,
4247 Operand((kStackFrameExtraParamSlot + 1) * kSystemPointerSize));
4248 __ StoreU64(central_stack_sp, MemOperand(fp, ExitFrameConstants::kSPOffset));
4249
4250 __ bind(&do_not_need_to_switch);
4251}
4252
4253void SwitchFromTheCentralStackIfNeeded(MacroAssembler* masm) {
4254 using ER = ExternalReference;
4255
4256 Label no_stack_change;
4257
4258 __ CmpU32(kSwitchFlagRegister, Operand(0), r0);
4259 __ bne(&no_stack_change);
4260
4261 {
4262 __ Push(kReturnRegister0, kReturnRegister1);
4263 __ PrepareCallCFunction(1, r0);
4264 __ Move(kCArgRegs[0], ER::isolate_address());
4265 __ CallCFunction(ER::wasm_switch_from_the_central_stack(), 1,
4266 SetIsolateDataSlots::kNo);
4267 __ Pop(kReturnRegister0, kReturnRegister1);
4268 }
4269
4270 __ Move(sp, kOldSPRegister);
4271
4272 __ bind(&no_stack_change);
4273}

4278
4279void Builtins::Generate_CEntry(MacroAssembler* masm, int result_size,
4280 ArgvMode argv_mode, bool builtin_exit_frame,
4281 bool switch_to_central_stack) {
4282 // Called from JavaScript; parameters are on stack as if calling JS function.
4283 // r3: number of arguments including receiver
4284 // r4: pointer to builtin function
4285 // fp: frame pointer (restored after C call)
4286 // sp: stack pointer (restored as callee's sp after C call)
4287 // cp: current context (C callee-saved)
4288 //
4289 // If argv_mode == ArgvMode::kRegister:
4290 // r5: pointer to the first argument
4291
4292 using ER = ExternalReference;
4293
4294 // Move input arguments to more convenient registers.
4295 static constexpr Register argc_input = r3;
4296 static constexpr Register target_fun = r15; // C callee-saved
4297 static constexpr Register argv = r4;
4298 static constexpr Register scratch = ip;
4299 static constexpr Register argc_sav = r14; // C callee-saved
4300
4301 __ mr(target_fun, argv);
4302
4303 if (argv_mode == ArgvMode::kRegister) {
4304 // Move argv into the correct register.
4305 __ mr(argv, r5);
4306 } else {
4307 // Compute the argv pointer.
4308 __ ShiftLeftU64(argv, argc_input, Operand(kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
4309 __ add(argv, argv, sp);
4310 __ subi(argv, argv, Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
4311 }
4312
4313 // Enter the exit frame that transitions from JavaScript to C++.
4314 FrameScope scope(masm, StackFrame::MANUAL);
4315
4316 int arg_stack_space = 0;
4317
4318 // Pass buffer for return value on stack if necessary
4319 bool needs_return_buffer =
4320 (result_size == 2 && !ABI_RETURNS_OBJECT_PAIRS_IN_REGS);
4321 if (needs_return_buffer) {
4322 arg_stack_space += result_size;
4323 }
4324
4325 __ EnterExitFrame(
4326 scratch, arg_stack_space,
4327 builtin_exit_frame ? StackFrame::BUILTIN_EXIT : StackFrame::EXIT);
4328
4329 // Store a copy of argc in callee-saved registers for later.
4330 __ mr(argc_sav, argc_input);
4331
4332 // r3: number of arguments including receiver
4333 // r14: number of arguments including receiver (C callee-saved)
4334 // r4: pointer to the first argument
4335 // r15: pointer to builtin function (C callee-saved)
4336
4337 // Result returned in registers or stack, depending on result size and ABI.
4338
4339 Register isolate_reg = r5;
4340 if (needs_return_buffer) {
4341 // The return value is a non-scalar value.
4342 // Use frame storage reserved by calling function to pass return
4343 // buffer as implicit first argument.
4344 __ mr(r5, r4);
4345 __ mr(r4, r3);
4346 __ addi(r3, sp,
4347 Operand((kStackFrameExtraParamSlot + 1) * kSystemPointerSize));
4348 isolate_reg = r6;
4349 }
4350
4351#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4352 if (switch_to_central_stack) {
4353 SwitchToTheCentralStackIfNeeded(masm, argc_input, target_fun, argv);
4354 }
4355#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4356
4357 // Call C built-in.
4358 __ Move(isolate_reg, ER::isolate_address());
4359 __ StoreReturnAddressAndCall(target_fun);
4360
4361#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4362 if (switch_to_central_stack) {
4363 SwitchFromTheCentralStackIfNeeded(masm);
4364 }
4365#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4366
4367 // If return value is on the stack, pop it to registers.
4368 if (needs_return_buffer) {
4369 __ LoadU64(r4, MemOperand(r3, kSystemPointerSize));
4370 __ LoadU64(r3, MemOperand(r3));
4371 }
4372
4373 // Check result for exception sentinel.
4374 Label exception_returned;
4375 __ CompareRoot(r3, RootIndex::kException);
4376 __ beq(&exception_returned);
4377
4378 // Check that there is no exception, otherwise we
4379 // should have returned the exception sentinel.
4380 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
4381 Label okay;
4382 ER exception_address =
4383 ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kExceptionAddress, masm->isolate());
4384 __ LoadU64(scratch,
4385 __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(exception_address, no_reg));
4386 __ LoadRoot(r0, RootIndex::kTheHoleValue);
4387 __ CompareTagged(r0, scratch);
4388 // Cannot use check here as it attempts to generate call into runtime.
4389 __ beq(&okay);
4390 __ stop();
4391 __ bind(&okay);
4392 }
4393
4394 // Exit C frame and return.
4395 // r3:r4: result
4396 // sp: stack pointer
4397 // fp: frame pointer
4398 // r14: still holds argc (C caller-saved).
4399 __ LeaveExitFrame(scratch);
4400 if (argv_mode == ArgvMode::kStack) {
4401 DCHECK(!AreAliased(scratch, argc_sav));
4402 __ ShiftLeftU64(scratch, argc_sav, Operand(kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
4403 __ AddS64(sp, sp, scratch);
4404 }
4405
4406 __ blr();
4407
4408 // Handling of exception.
4409 __ bind(&exception_returned);
4410
4411 ER pending_handler_context_address = ER::Create(
4412 IsolateAddressId::kPendingHandlerContextAddress, masm->isolate());
4413 ER pending_handler_entrypoint_address = ER::Create(
4414 IsolateAddressId::kPendingHandlerEntrypointAddress, masm->isolate());
4415 ER pending_handler_constant_pool_address = ER::Create(
4416 IsolateAddressId::kPendingHandlerConstantPoolAddress, masm->isolate());
4417 ER pending_handler_fp_address =
4418 ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kPendingHandlerFPAddress, masm->isolate());
4419 ER pending_handler_sp_address =
4420 ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kPendingHandlerSPAddress, masm->isolate());
4421
4422 // Ask the runtime for help to determine the handler. This will set r3 to
4423 // contain the current exception, don't clobber it.
4424 {
4425 FrameScope scope(masm, StackFrame::MANUAL);
4426 __ PrepareCallCFunction(3, 0, r3);
4427 __ li(kCArgRegs[0], Operand::Zero());
4428 __ li(kCArgRegs[1], Operand::Zero());
4429 __ Move(kCArgRegs[2], ER::isolate_address());
4430 __ CallCFunction(ER::Create(Runtime::kUnwindAndFindExceptionHandler), 3,
4431 SetIsolateDataSlots::kNo);
4432 }
4433
4434 // Retrieve the handler context, SP and FP.
4435 __ Move(cp, pending_handler_context_address);
4436 __ LoadU64(cp, MemOperand(cp));
4437 __ Move(sp, pending_handler_sp_address);
4438 __ LoadU64(sp, MemOperand(sp));
4439 __ Move(fp, pending_handler_fp_address);
4440 __ LoadU64(fp, MemOperand(fp));
4441
4442 // If the handler is a JS frame, restore the context to the frame. Note that
4443 // the context will be set to (cp == 0) for non-JS frames.
4444 Label skip;
4445 __ cmpi(cp, Operand::Zero());
4446 __ beq(&skip);
4447 __ StoreU64(cp, MemOperand(fp, StandardFrameConstants::kContextOffset));
4448 __ bind(&skip);
4449
4450 // Clear c_entry_fp, like we do in `LeaveExitFrame`.
4451 ER c_entry_fp_address =
4452 ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kCEntryFPAddress, masm->isolate());
4453 __ mov(scratch, Operand::Zero());
4454 __ StoreU64(scratch,
4455 __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(c_entry_fp_address, no_reg));
4456
4457 // Compute the handler entry address and jump to it.
4458 ConstantPoolUnavailableScope constant_pool_unavailable(masm);
4459 __ LoadU64(
4460 scratch,
4461 __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(pending_handler_entrypoint_address, no_reg),
4462 r0);
4463 if (V8_EMBEDDED_CONSTANT_POOL_BOOL) {
4464 __ Move(kConstantPoolRegister, pending_handler_constant_pool_address);
4465 __ LoadU64(kConstantPoolRegister, MemOperand(kConstantPoolRegister));
4466 }
4467 __ Jump(scratch);
4468}

4471void Builtins::Generate_WasmHandleStackOverflow(MacroAssembler* masm) {
4472 __ Trap();
4473}
