4475
4476void Builtins::Generate_DoubleToI(MacroAssembler* masm) {
4477 Label out_of_range, only_low, negate, done, fastpath_done;
4478 Register result_reg = r3;
4479
4480 HardAbortScope hard_abort(masm); // Avoid calls to Abort.
4481
4482 // Immediate values for this stub fit in instructions, so it's safe to use ip.
4483 Register scratch = GetRegisterThatIsNotOneOf(result_reg);
4484 Register scratch_low = GetRegisterThatIsNotOneOf(result_reg, scratch);
4485 Register scratch_high =
4486 GetRegisterThatIsNotOneOf(result_reg, scratch, scratch_low);
4487 DoubleRegister double_scratch = kScratchDoubleReg;
4488
4489 __ Push(result_reg, scratch);
4490 // Account for saved regs.
4491 int argument_offset = 2 * kSystemPointerSize;
4492
4493 // Load double input.
4494 __ lfd(double_scratch, MemOperand(sp, argument_offset));
4495
4496 // Do fast-path convert from double to int.
4497 __ ConvertDoubleToInt64(double_scratch,
4498 result_reg, d0);
4499
4500// Test for overflow
4501 __ TestIfInt32(result_reg, r0);
4502 __ beq(&fastpath_done);
4503
4504 __ Push(scratch_high, scratch_low);
4505 // Account for saved regs.
4506 argument_offset += 2 * kSystemPointerSize;
4507
4508 __ lwz(scratch_high,
4509 MemOperand(sp, argument_offset + Register::kExponentOffset));
4510 __ lwz(scratch_low,
4511 MemOperand(sp, argument_offset + Register::kMantissaOffset));
4512
4513 __ ExtractBitMask(scratch, scratch_high, HeapNumber::kExponentMask);
4514 // Load scratch with exponent - 1. This is faster than loading
4515 // with exponent because Bias + 1 = 1024 which is a *PPC* immediate value.
4516 static_assert(HeapNumber::kExponentBias + 1 == 1024);
4517 __ subi(scratch, scratch, Operand(HeapNumber::kExponentBias + 1));
4518 // If exponent is greater than or equal to 84, the 32 less significant
4519 // bits are 0s (2^84 = 1, 52 significant bits, 32 uncoded bits),
4520 // the result is 0.
4521 // Compare exponent with 84 (compare exponent - 1 with 83).
4522 __ cmpi(scratch, Operand(83));
4523 __ bge(&out_of_range);
4524
4525 // If we reach this code, 31 <= exponent <= 83.
4526 // So, we don't have to handle cases where 0 <= exponent <= 20 for
4527 // which we would need to shift right the high part of the mantissa.
4528 // Scratch contains exponent - 1.
4529 // Load scratch with 52 - exponent (load with 51 - (exponent - 1)).
4530 __ subfic(scratch, scratch, Operand(51));
4531 __ cmpi(scratch, Operand::Zero());
4532 __ ble(&only_low);
4533 // 21 <= exponent <= 51, shift scratch_low and scratch_high
4534 // to generate the result.
4535 __ srw(scratch_low, scratch_low, scratch);
4536 // Scratch contains: 52 - exponent.
4537 // We needs: exponent - 20.
4538 // So we use: 32 - scratch = 32 - 52 + exponent = exponent - 20.
4539 __ subfic(scratch, scratch, Operand(32));
4540 __ ExtractBitMask(result_reg, scratch_high, HeapNumber::kMantissaMask);
4541 // Set the implicit 1 before the mantissa part in scratch_high.
4542 static_assert(HeapNumber::kMantissaBitsInTopWord >= 16);
4543 __ oris(result_reg, result_reg,
4544 Operand(1 << ((HeapNumber::kMantissaBitsInTopWord)-16)));
4545 __ ShiftLeftU32(r0, result_reg, scratch);
4546 __ orx(result_reg, scratch_low, r0);
4547 __ b(&negate);
4548
4549 __ bind(&out_of_range);
4550 __ mov(result_reg, Operand::Zero());
4551 __ b(&done);
4552
4553 __ bind(&only_low);
4554 // 52 <= exponent <= 83, shift only scratch_low.
4555 // On entry, scratch contains: 52 - exponent.
4556 __ neg(scratch, scratch);
4557 __ ShiftLeftU32(result_reg, scratch_low, scratch);
4558
4559 __ bind(&negate);
4560 // If input was positive, scratch_high ASR 31 equals 0 and
4561 // scratch_high LSR 31 equals zero.
4562 // New result = (result eor 0) + 0 = result.
4563 // If the input was negative, we have to negate the result.
4564 // Input_high ASR 31 equals 0xFFFFFFFF and scratch_high LSR 31 equals 1.
4565 // New result = (result eor 0xFFFFFFFF) + 1 = 0 - result.
4566 __ srawi(r0, scratch_high, 31);
4567 __ srdi(r0, r0, Operand(32));
4568 __ xor_(result_reg, result_reg, r0);
4569 __ srwi(r0, scratch_high, Operand(31));
4570 __ add(result_reg, result_reg, r0);
4571
4572 __ bind(&done);
4573 __ Pop(scratch_high, scratch_low);
4574 // Account for saved regs.
4575 argument_offset -= 2 * kSystemPointerSize;
4576
4577 __ bind(&fastpath_done);
4578 __ StoreU64(result_reg, MemOperand(sp, argument_offset));
4579 __ Pop(result_reg, scratch);
4580
4581 __ Ret();
4582}
4583
4584void Builtins::Generate_CallApiCallbackImpl(MacroAssembler* masm,
4585 CallApiCallbackMode mode) {
4586 // ----------- S t a t e -------------
4587 // CallApiCallbackMode::kOptimizedNoProfiling/kOptimized modes:
4588 // -- r4 : api function address
4589 // Both modes:
4590 // -- r5 : arguments count (not including the receiver)
4591 // -- r6 : FunctionTemplateInfo
4592 // -- r3 : holder
4593 // -- cp : context
4594 // -- sp[0] : receiver
4595 // -- sp[8] : first argument
4596 // -- ...
4597 // -- sp[(argc) * 8] : last argument
4598 // -----------------------------------
4599
4600 Register function_callback_info_arg = kCArgRegs[0];
4601
4602 Register api_function_address = no_reg;
4603 Register argc = no_reg;
4604 Register func_templ = no_reg;
4605 Register holder = no_reg;
4606 Register topmost_script_having_context = no_reg;
4607 Register scratch = r7;
4608
4609 switch (mode) {
4610 case CallApiCallbackMode::kGeneric:
4611 argc = CallApiCallbackGenericDescriptor::ActualArgumentsCountRegister();
4612 topmost_script_having_context = CallApiCallbackGenericDescriptor::
4613 TopmostScriptHavingContextRegister();
4614 func_templ =
4615 CallApiCallbackGenericDescriptor::FunctionTemplateInfoRegister();
4616 holder = CallApiCallbackGenericDescriptor::HolderRegister();
4617 break;
4618
4619 case CallApiCallbackMode::kOptimizedNoProfiling:
4620 case CallApiCallbackMode::kOptimized:
4621 // Caller context is always equal to current context because we don't
4622 // inline Api calls cross-context.
4623 topmost_script_having_context = kContextRegister;
4624 api_function_address =
4625 CallApiCallbackOptimizedDescriptor::ApiFunctionAddressRegister();
4626 argc = CallApiCallbackOptimizedDescriptor::ActualArgumentsCountRegister();
4627 func_templ =
4628 CallApiCallbackOptimizedDescriptor::FunctionTemplateInfoRegister();
4629 holder = CallApiCallbackOptimizedDescriptor::HolderRegister();
4630 break;
4631 }
4632 DCHECK(!AreAliased(api_function_address, topmost_script_having_context, argc,
4633 holder, func_templ, scratch));
4634
4635 using FCA = FunctionCallbackArguments;
4636 using ER = ExternalReference;
4637 using FC = ApiCallbackExitFrameConstants;
4638
4639 static_assert(FCA::kArgsLength == 6);
4640 static_assert(FCA::kNewTargetIndex == 5);
4641 static_assert(FCA::kTargetIndex == 4);
4642 static_assert(FCA::kReturnValueIndex == 3);
4643 static_assert(FCA::kContextIndex == 2);
4644 static_assert(FCA::kIsolateIndex == 1);
4645 static_assert(FCA::kHolderIndex == 0);
4646
4647 // Set up FunctionCallbackInfo's implicit_args on the stack as follows:
4648 //
4649 // Target state:
4650 // sp[1 * kSystemPointerSize]: kHolder <= FCA::implicit_args_
4651 // sp[2 * kSystemPointerSize]: kIsolate
4652 // sp[3 * kSystemPointerSize]: kContext
4653 // sp[4 * kSystemPointerSize]: undefined (kReturnValue)
4654 // sp[5 * kSystemPointerSize]: kTarget
4655 // sp[6 * kSystemPointerSize]: undefined (kNewTarget)
4656 // Existing state:
4657 // sp[7 * kSystemPointerSize]: <= FCA:::values_
4658
4659 __ StoreRootRelative(IsolateData::topmost_script_having_context_offset(),
4660 topmost_script_having_context);
4661
4662 if (mode == CallApiCallbackMode::kGeneric) {
4663 api_function_address = ReassignRegister(topmost_script_having_context);
4664 }
4665
4666 // Reserve space on the stack.
4667 __ subi(sp, sp, Operand(FCA::kArgsLength * kSystemPointerSize));
4668
4669 // kHolder.
4670 __ StoreU64(holder, MemOperand(sp, FCA::kHolderIndex * kSystemPointerSize));
4671
4672 // kIsolate.
4673 __ Move(scratch, ER::isolate_address());
4674 __ StoreU64(scratch, MemOperand(sp, FCA::kIsolateIndex * kSystemPointerSize));
4675
4676 // kContext
4677 __ StoreU64(cp, MemOperand(sp, FCA::kContextIndex * kSystemPointerSize));
4678
4679 // kReturnValue.
4680 __ LoadRoot(scratch, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
4681 __ StoreU64(scratch,
4682 MemOperand(sp, FCA::kReturnValueIndex * kSystemPointerSize));
4683
4684 // kTarget.
4685 __ StoreU64(func_templ,
4686 MemOperand(sp, FCA::kTargetIndex * kSystemPointerSize));
4687
4688 // kNewTarget.
4689 __ StoreU64(scratch,
4690 MemOperand(sp, FCA::kNewTargetIndex * kSystemPointerSize));
4691
4692 FrameScope frame_scope(masm, StackFrame::MANUAL);
4693 if (mode == CallApiCallbackMode::kGeneric) {
4694 __ LoadExternalPointerField(
4695 api_function_address,
4696 FieldMemOperand(func_templ,
4697 FunctionTemplateInfo::kMaybeRedirectedCallbackOffset),
4698 kFunctionTemplateInfoCallbackTag, no_reg, scratch);
4699 }
4700 __ EnterExitFrame(scratch, FC::getExtraSlotsCountFrom<ExitFrameConstants>(),
4701 StackFrame::API_CALLBACK_EXIT);
4702
4703 MemOperand argc_operand = MemOperand(fp, FC::kFCIArgcOffset);
4704 {
4705 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm, "Initialize v8::FunctionCallbackInfo");
4706 // FunctionCallbackInfo::length_.
4707 // TODO(ishell): pass JSParameterCount(argc) to simplify things on the
4708 // caller end.
4709 __ StoreU64(argc, argc_operand);
4710
4711 // FunctionCallbackInfo::implicit_args_.
4712 __ AddS64(scratch, fp, Operand(FC::kImplicitArgsArrayOffset));
4713 __ StoreU64(scratch, MemOperand(fp, FC::kFCIImplicitArgsOffset));
4714
4715 // FunctionCallbackInfo::values_ (points at JS arguments on the stack).
4716 __ AddS64(scratch, fp, Operand(FC::kFirstArgumentOffset));
4717 __ StoreU64(scratch, MemOperand(fp, FC::kFCIValuesOffset));
4718 }
4719
4720 __ RecordComment("v8::FunctionCallback's argument");
4721 __ AddS64(function_callback_info_arg, fp,
4722 Operand(FC::kFunctionCallbackInfoOffset));
4723
4724 DCHECK(!AreAliased(api_function_address, function_callback_info_arg));
4725
4726 ExternalReference thunk_ref = ER::invoke_function_callback(mode);
4727 Register no_thunk_arg = no_reg;
4728
4729 MemOperand return_value_operand = MemOperand(fp, FC::kReturnValueOffset);
4730 static constexpr int kSlotsToDropOnReturn =
4731 FC::kFunctionCallbackInfoArgsLength + kJSArgcReceiverSlots;
4732
4733 const bool with_profiling =
4734 mode != CallApiCallbackMode::kOptimizedNoProfiling;
4735 CallApiFunctionAndReturn(masm, with_profiling, api_function_address,
4736 thunk_ref, no_thunk_arg, kSlotsToDropOnReturn,
4737 &argc_operand, return_value_operand);
4738}

4740void Builtins::Generate_CallApiGetter(MacroAssembler* masm) {
4741 // ----------- S t a t e -------------
4742 // -- cp : context
4743 // -- r4 : receiver
4744 // -- r6 : accessor info
4745 // -- r3 : holder
4746 // -----------------------------------
4747
4748 // Build v8::PropertyCallbackInfo::args_ array on the stack and push property
4749 // name below the exit frame to make GC aware of them.
4750 using PCA = PropertyCallbackArguments;
4751 using ER = ExternalReference;
4752 using FC = ApiAccessorExitFrameConstants;
4753
4754 static_assert(PCA::kPropertyKeyIndex == 0);
4755 static_assert(PCA::kShouldThrowOnErrorIndex == 1);
4756 static_assert(PCA::kHolderIndex == 2);
4757 static_assert(PCA::kIsolateIndex == 3);
4758 static_assert(PCA::kHolderV2Index == 4);
4759 static_assert(PCA::kReturnValueIndex == 5);
4760 static_assert(PCA::kDataIndex == 6);
4761 static_assert(PCA::kThisIndex == 7);
4762 static_assert(PCA::kArgsLength == 8);
4763
4764 // Set up v8::PropertyCallbackInfo's (PCI) args_ on the stack as follows:
4765 // Target state:
4766 // sp[0 * kSystemPointerSize]: name <= PCI::args_
4767 // sp[1 * kSystemPointerSize]: kShouldThrowOnErrorIndex
4768 // sp[2 * kSystemPointerSize]: kHolderIndex
4769 // sp[3 * kSystemPointerSize]: kIsolateIndex
4770 // sp[4 * kSystemPointerSize]: kHolderV2Index
4771 // sp[5 * kSystemPointerSize]: kReturnValueIndex
4772 // sp[6 * kSystemPointerSize]: kDataIndex
4773 // sp[7 * kSystemPointerSize]: kThisIndex / receiver
4774
4775 Register name_arg = kCArgRegs[0];
4776 Register property_callback_info_arg = kCArgRegs[1];
4777
4778 Register api_function_address = r5;
4779 Register receiver = ApiGetterDescriptor::ReceiverRegister();
4780 Register holder = ApiGetterDescriptor::HolderRegister();
4781 Register callback = ApiGetterDescriptor::CallbackRegister();
4782 Register scratch = r7;
4783 Register smi_zero = r8;
4784
4785 DCHECK(!AreAliased(receiver, holder, callback, scratch, smi_zero));
4786
4787 __ LoadTaggedField(scratch,
4788 FieldMemOperand(callback, AccessorInfo::kDataOffset), r0);
4789 __ Push(receiver, scratch); // kThisIndex, kDataIndex
4790 __ LoadRoot(scratch, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
4791 __ Move(smi_zero, Smi::zero());
4792 __ Push(scratch, smi_zero); // kReturnValueIndex, kHolderV2Index
4793 __ Move(scratch, ER::isolate_address());
4794 __ Push(scratch, holder); // kIsolateIndex, kHolderIndex
4795
4796 __ LoadTaggedField(name_arg,
4797 FieldMemOperand(callback, AccessorInfo::kNameOffset), r0);
4798 static_assert(kDontThrow == 0);
4799 __ Push(smi_zero, name_arg); // should_throw_on_error -> kDontThrow, name
4800
4801 __ RecordComment("Load api_function_address");
4802 __ LoadExternalPointerField(
4803 api_function_address,
4804 FieldMemOperand(callback, AccessorInfo::kMaybeRedirectedGetterOffset),
4805 kAccessorInfoGetterTag, no_reg, scratch);
4806
4807 FrameScope frame_scope(masm, StackFrame::MANUAL);
4808 __ EnterExitFrame(scratch, FC::getExtraSlotsCountFrom<ExitFrameConstants>(),
4809 StackFrame::API_ACCESSOR_EXIT);
4810
4811 __ RecordComment("Create v8::PropertyCallbackInfo object on the stack.");
4812 // property_callback_info_arg = v8::PropertyCallbackInfo&
4813 __ AddS64(property_callback_info_arg, fp, Operand(FC::kArgsArrayOffset));
4814
4815 DCHECK(!AreAliased(api_function_address, property_callback_info_arg, name_arg,
4816 callback, scratch));
4817
4818#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DIRECT_HANDLE
4819 // name_arg = Local<Name>(name), name value was pushed to GC-ed stack space.
4820 // |name_arg| is already initialized above.
4821#else
4822 // name_arg = Local<Name>(&name), which is &args_array[kPropertyKeyIndex].
4823 static_assert(PCA::kPropertyKeyIndex == 0);
4824 __ mr(name_arg, property_callback_info_arg);
4825#endif
4826
4827 ExternalReference thunk_ref = ER::invoke_accessor_getter_callback();
4828 // Pass AccessorInfo to thunk wrapper in case profiler or side-effect
4829 // checking is enabled.
4830 Register thunk_arg = callback;
4831
4832 MemOperand return_value_operand = MemOperand(fp, FC::kReturnValueOffset);
4833 static constexpr int kSlotsToDropOnReturn =
4834 FC::kPropertyCallbackInfoArgsLength;
4835 MemOperand* const kUseStackSpaceConstant = nullptr;
4836
4837 const bool with_profiling = true;
4838 CallApiFunctionAndReturn(masm, with_profiling, api_function_address,
4839 thunk_ref, thunk_arg, kSlotsToDropOnReturn,
4840 kUseStackSpaceConstant, return_value_operand);
4841}
4842
4843void Builtins::Generate_DirectCEntry(MacroAssembler* masm) {
4844 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm);
4845 Register temp2 = temps.Acquire();
4846 // Place the return address on the stack, making the call
4847 // GC safe. The RegExp backend also relies on this.
4848 __ mflr(r0);
4849 __ StoreU64(r0,
4850 MemOperand(sp, kStackFrameExtraParamSlot * kSystemPointerSize));
4851
4852 if (ABI_USES_FUNCTION_DESCRIPTORS) {
4853 // AIX/PPC64BE Linux use a function descriptor;
4854 __ LoadU64(ToRegister(ABI_TOC_REGISTER),
4855 MemOperand(temp2, kSystemPointerSize));
4856 __ LoadU64(temp2, MemOperand(temp2, 0)); // Instruction address
4857 }
4858
4859 __ Call(temp2); // Call the C++ function.
4860 __ LoadU64(r0,
4861 MemOperand(sp, kStackFrameExtraParamSlot * kSystemPointerSize));
4862 __ mtlr(r0);
4863 __ blr();
4864}

4866namespace {
4867
4868// This code tries to be close to ia32 code so that any changes can be
4869// easily ported.
4870void Generate_DeoptimizationEntry(MacroAssembler* masm,
4871 DeoptimizeKind deopt_kind) {
4872 Isolate* isolate = masm->isolate();
4873
4874 // Unlike on ARM we don't save all the registers, just the useful ones.
4875 // For the rest, there are gaps on the stack, so the offsets remain the same.
4876 const int kNumberOfRegisters = Register::kNumRegisters;
4877
4878 RegList restored_regs = kJSCallerSaved | kCalleeSaved;
4879 RegList saved_regs = restored_regs | sp;
4880
4881 const int kDoubleRegsSize = kDoubleSize * DoubleRegister::kNumRegisters;
4882
4883 // Save all double registers before messing with them.
4884 __ subi(sp, sp, Operand(kDoubleRegsSize));
4885 const RegisterConfiguration* config = RegisterConfiguration::Default();
4886 for (int i = 0; i < config->num_allocatable_double_registers(); ++i) {
4887 int code = config->GetAllocatableDoubleCode(i);
4888 const DoubleRegister dreg = DoubleRegister::from_code(code);
4889 int offset = code * kDoubleSize;
4890 __ stfd(dreg, MemOperand(sp, offset));
4891 }
4892
4893 // Push saved_regs (needed to populate FrameDescription::registers_).
4894 // Leave gaps for other registers.
4895 __ subi(sp, sp, Operand(kNumberOfRegisters * kSystemPointerSize));
4896 for (int16_t i = kNumberOfRegisters - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
4897 if ((saved_regs.bits() & (1 << i)) != 0) {
4898 __ StoreU64(ToRegister(i), MemOperand(sp, kSystemPointerSize * i));
4899 }
4900 }
4901 {
4902 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm);
4903 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4904 __ Move(scratch, ExternalReference::Create(
4905 IsolateAddressId::kCEntryFPAddress, isolate));
4906 __ StoreU64(fp, MemOperand(scratch));
4907 }
4908 const int kSavedRegistersAreaSize =
4909 (kNumberOfRegisters * kSystemPointerSize) + kDoubleRegsSize;
4910
4911 // Get the address of the location in the code object (r6) (return
4912 // address for lazy deoptimization) and compute the fp-to-sp delta in
4913 // register r7.
4914 __ mflr(r5);
4915 __ addi(r6, sp, Operand(kSavedRegistersAreaSize));
4916 __ sub(r6, fp, r6);
4917
4918 // Allocate a new deoptimizer object.
4919 // Pass six arguments in r3 to r8.
4920 __ PrepareCallCFunction(5, r8);
4921 __ li(r3, Operand::Zero());
4922 Label context_check;
4923 __ LoadU64(r4,
4924 MemOperand(fp, CommonFrameConstants::kContextOrFrameTypeOffset));
4925 __ JumpIfSmi(r4, &context_check);
4926 __ LoadU64(r3, MemOperand(fp, StandardFrameConstants::kFunctionOffset));
4927 __ bind(&context_check);
4928 __ li(r4, Operand(static_cast<int>(deopt_kind)));
4929 // r5: code address or 0 already loaded.
4930 // r6: Fp-to-sp delta already loaded.
4931 __ Move(r7, ExternalReference::isolate_address());
4932 // Call Deoptimizer::New().
4933 {
4934 AllowExternalCallThatCantCauseGC scope(masm);
4935 __ CallCFunction(ExternalReference::new_deoptimizer_function(), 5);
4936 }
4937
4938 // Preserve "deoptimizer" object in register r3 and get the input
4939 // frame descriptor pointer to r4 (deoptimizer->input_);
4940 __ LoadU64(r4, MemOperand(r3, Deoptimizer::input_offset()));
4941
4942 // Copy core registers into FrameDescription::registers_[kNumRegisters].
4943 DCHECK_EQ(Register::kNumRegisters, kNumberOfRegisters);
4944 for (int i = 0; i < kNumberOfRegisters; i++) {
4945 int offset =
4946 (i * kSystemPointerSize) + FrameDescription::registers_offset();
4947 __ LoadU64(r5, MemOperand(sp, i * kSystemPointerSize));
4948 __ StoreU64(r5, MemOperand(r4, offset));
4949 }
4950
4951 int simd128_regs_offset = FrameDescription::simd128_registers_offset();
4952 // Copy double registers to
4953 // double_registers_[DoubleRegister::kNumRegisters]
4954 for (int i = 0; i < config->num_allocatable_double_registers(); ++i) {
4955 int code = config->GetAllocatableDoubleCode(i);
4956 int dst_offset = code * kSimd128Size + simd128_regs_offset;
4957 int src_offset =
4958 code * kDoubleSize + kNumberOfRegisters * kSystemPointerSize;
4959 __ lfd(d0, MemOperand(sp, src_offset));
4960 __ stfd(d0, MemOperand(r4, dst_offset));
4961 }
4962
4963 // Mark the stack as not iterable for the CPU profiler which won't be able to
4964 // walk the stack without the return address.
4965 {
4966 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm);
4967 Register is_iterable = temps.Acquire();
4968 Register zero = r7;
4969 __ LoadIsolateField(is_iterable, IsolateFieldId::kStackIsIterable);
4970 __ li(zero, Operand(0));
4971 __ stb(zero, MemOperand(is_iterable));
4972 }
4973
4974 // Remove the saved registers from the stack.
4975 __ addi(sp, sp, Operand(kSavedRegistersAreaSize));
4976
4977 // Compute a pointer to the unwinding limit in register r5; that is
4978 // the first stack slot not part of the input frame.
4979 __ LoadU64(r5, MemOperand(r4, FrameDescription::frame_size_offset()));
4980 __ add(r5, r5, sp);
4981
4982 // Unwind the stack down to - but not including - the unwinding
4983 // limit and copy the contents of the activation frame to the input
4984 // frame description.
4985 __ addi(r6, r4, Operand(FrameDescription::frame_content_offset()));
4986 Label pop_loop;
4987 Label pop_loop_header;
4988 __ b(&pop_loop_header);
4989 __ bind(&pop_loop);
4990 __ pop(r7);
4991 __ StoreU64(r7, MemOperand(r6, 0));
4992 __ addi(r6, r6, Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
4993 __ bind(&pop_loop_header);
4994 __ CmpS64(r5, sp);
4995 __ bne(&pop_loop);
4996
4997 // Compute the output frame in the deoptimizer.
4998 __ push(r3); // Preserve deoptimizer object across call.
4999 // r3: deoptimizer object; r4: scratch.
5000 __ PrepareCallCFunction(1, r4);
5001 // Call Deoptimizer::ComputeOutputFrames().
5002 {
5003 AllowExternalCallThatCantCauseGC scope(masm);
5004 __ CallCFunction(ExternalReference::compute_output_frames_function(), 1);
5005 }
5006 __ pop(r3); // Restore deoptimizer object (class Deoptimizer).
5007
5008 __ LoadU64(sp, MemOperand(r3, Deoptimizer::caller_frame_top_offset()));
5009
5010 // Replace the current (input) frame with the output frames.
5011 Label outer_push_loop, inner_push_loop, outer_loop_header, inner_loop_header;
5012 // Outer loop state: r7 = current "FrameDescription** output_",
5013 // r4 = one past the last FrameDescription**.
5014 __ lwz(r4, MemOperand(r3, Deoptimizer::output_count_offset()));
5015 __ LoadU64(r7,
5016 MemOperand(r3, Deoptimizer::output_offset())); // r7 is output_.
5017 __ ShiftLeftU64(r4, r4, Operand(kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
5018 __ add(r4, r7, r4);
5019 __ b(&outer_loop_header);
5020
5021 __ bind(&outer_push_loop);
5022 // Inner loop state: r5 = current FrameDescription*, r6 = loop index.
5023 __ LoadU64(r5, MemOperand(r7, 0)); // output_[ix]
5024 __ LoadU64(r6, MemOperand(r5, FrameDescription::frame_size_offset()));
5025 __ b(&inner_loop_header);
5026
5027 __ bind(&inner_push_loop);
5028 __ addi(r6, r6, Operand(-sizeof(intptr_t)));
5029 __ add(r9, r5, r6);
5030 __ LoadU64(r9, MemOperand(r9, FrameDescription::frame_content_offset()));
5031 __ push(r9);
5032
5033 __ bind(&inner_loop_header);
5034 __ cmpi(r6, Operand::Zero());
5035 __ bne(&inner_push_loop); // test for gt?
5036
5037 __ addi(r7, r7, Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
5038 __ bind(&outer_loop_header);
5039 __ CmpS64(r7, r4);
5040 __ blt(&outer_push_loop);
5041
5042 __ LoadU64(r4, MemOperand(r3, Deoptimizer::input_offset()));
5043 for (int i = 0; i < config->num_allocatable_double_registers(); ++i) {
5044 int code = config->GetAllocatableDoubleCode(i);
5045 const DoubleRegister dreg = DoubleRegister::from_code(code);
5046 int src_offset = code * kSimd128Size + simd128_regs_offset;
5047 __ lfd(dreg, MemOperand(r4, src_offset));
5048 }
5049
5050 // Push pc, and continuation from the last output frame.
5051 __ LoadU64(r9, MemOperand(r5, FrameDescription::pc_offset()));
5052 __ push(r9);
5053 __ LoadU64(r9, MemOperand(r5, FrameDescription::continuation_offset()));
5054 __ push(r9);
5055
5056 // Restore the registers from the last output frame.
5057 {
5058 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm);
5059 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5060 DCHECK(!(restored_regs.has(scratch)));
5061 __ mr(scratch, r5);
5062 for (int i = kNumberOfRegisters - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
5063 int offset =
5064 (i * kSystemPointerSize) + FrameDescription::registers_offset();
5065 if ((restored_regs.bits() & (1 << i)) != 0) {
5066 __ LoadU64(ToRegister(i), MemOperand(scratch, offset));
5067 }
5068 }
5069 }
5070
5071 {
5072 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm);
5073 Register is_iterable = temps.Acquire();
5074 Register one = r7;
5075 __ push(one); // Save the value from the output FrameDescription.
5076 __ LoadIsolateField(is_iterable, IsolateFieldId::kStackIsIterable);
5077 __ li(one, Operand(1));
5078 __ stb(one, MemOperand(is_iterable));
5079 __ pop(one); // Restore the value from the output FrameDescription.
5080 }
5081
5082 {
5083 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm);
5084 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5085 __ pop(scratch); // get continuation, leave pc on stack
5086 __ pop(r0);
5087 __ mtlr(r0);
5088 Label end;
5089 __ CmpU64(scratch, Operand::Zero(), r0);
5090 __ beq(&end);
5091 __ Jump(scratch);
5092 __ bind(&end);
5093 __ Ret();
5094 }
5095
5096 __ stop();
5097}

5109void Builtins::Generate_RestartFrameTrampoline(MacroAssembler* masm) {
5110 // Frame is being dropped:
5111 // - Look up current function on the frame.
5112 // - Leave the frame.
5113 // - Restart the frame by calling the function.
5114
5115 __ LoadU64(r4, MemOperand(fp, StandardFrameConstants::kFunctionOffset));
5116 __ LoadU64(r3, MemOperand(fp, StandardFrameConstants::kArgCOffset));
5117 __ LeaveFrame(StackFrame::INTERPRETED);
5118
5119 // The arguments are already in the stack (including any necessary padding),
5120 // we should not try to massage the arguments again.
5121 __ mov(r5, Operand(kDontAdaptArgumentsSentinel));
5122 __ InvokeFunction(r4, r5, r3, InvokeType::kJump);
5123}
